text: there can be alot of confusion on the journey of spiritual awakening. i have experienced much of it. these days, i feel so much clearer than i ever have before. within myself and my life. i have learnt inner discernment and it came about through some unfortunate circumstances in my life. when i trusted too quickly and let my guard down. there were many experiences where i have been taken advantage of and many "leaders" and "shamans/gurus" attempted to destroy my light... i could easily name a few in the spiritual community that would destroy their reputation... ones that live in the byron bay community.. and that doesn't feel in integrity with me. i told who i needed to for protection and to protect others so they don't have to go through what i went through. i have experienced physical, sexual, emotional, mental, spiritual abuse. from many different beings from many different circumstances. i don't wish this upon anyone. yet so many go through this too. even though it was deeply traumatising, many many gifts have come from them. if you have been through abuse, do not spiritually bypass and ignore it. you deserve a safe and sacred space to be heard, to be felt, to be loved for what you went through. it's not your fault, but it is your responsibility to heal. you don't have to suffer beloved. it's time to speak up, tell your story. write it out, cry it out, dance it out.. seek professional help. invest in yourself.. i am hesitant sharing this because its incredibly vulnerable.. yet its important.. i have the privilege of using my voice and i will not take it for granted. with love, abby x

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytica $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
on my first love:

hold still. this might hurt a little. this is love. this is the tide turning, skull burning intergalactic love you read about as a child. the love of heathcliff and catherine running in the moors. the love of alice and her mad hatter. the love you imagined with barbie and ken in hand. hold still. this might sting a little. like a bees last defiant act of self love. you will do the same for him, you will lose your stinger, lose your heart, lose your mind, to keep him from harm. hold still. for holding still is the only way to catch it all, that crooked smile of his, the urgent kisses, the sleepy morning talks. this is the ‘top of the ferris wheel’ kind of love, the ‘lets jump in that puddle’ kind of love, this is the passionate screaming, midnight loving kind of love. hold still. don’t run, don’t hide, it will find you either way my darling. hold still. let it get you. let it overwhelm you. let yourself fall hard, into the rabbit hole. it will pick you up, it will heal you, it will keep you safe. hold still. this is love.

text: 🏋🏼‍♀️ becks here! recently back in the fitness game. 3 years ago i suffered a spinal cord injury that left me a partial paraplegic. i gained a lot of weight from lack of movement and poor eating habits. working on bettering myself by lifting heavy things and making good nutritional choices. 🏋️‍♀️ hey y'all i'm jojo! i'm a semi-newbie to weight lifting. joining the gym last year came with a lot of anxiety for me. i had gained a lot of weight while healing mentally and physically from a major trauma. i was working through depression and controlling anxiety. my big progress so far is being medication free, mentally strong and secure in work towards my happy healthy goals! 💋💋 let us know if you have any questions! hope you follow us on our journey! ➡️➡️

text:
we have the great pleasure this year to welcome blo vancouver owner jenny randhawa to our program this year - this has been in the works for a long time, and we're so glad to pass you the mic! .
.
jenny graduated with a master's in health administration from ubc in 2005. with eight years of management consulting experience, a strong background of education and practical experience, it’s no wonder that she has become a force to be reckoned with in the business world. in 2007 jenny decided to tackle new territory — the beauty industry. when blo blow dry bar launched in 2007, jenny was the first to be considered for a franchise partnership and has been with the company since day one, savouring the successes and learning and perfecting the ropes. following the success of her first bar in early 2010, jenny acquired all 3 of vancouver’s blo bars six months later as well as the rights to all of british columbia, striking while the (curling) iron was hot! since then, jenny continues to lead this multi-unit company demonstrating her strengths in all aspects of business management including operations, efficency, growth strategy, conflict resolution, brand and culture management, organizational structure as well as strategic planning. in 2019, blo corporate recognized her as a leading franchise partner out of 130+ blo locations in social media management, staff management, retention and culture and outstanding contributor to operational growth strategies. her greatest passion is to provide one-on-one support and guidance to her fellow entrepreneurs.
.
. 
the well beings & weekend rituals (march 4, 9 & 10)
https://iwd2019vancouver.eventbrite.ca or the link in @minibarcanada’s profile.

text:
consider this!!!!! self-love is one of the most important attributes for success and a key to breaking toxic cycles. it allows us to achieve more and live a healthy life with inner peace. the better you feel about yourself, the more you can accomplish. so, we want the best for our children, therefore, we must instill self-love into them as early as possible. not only does it help them accomplish their goals and dreams, but it's a protection for them as well. *********
join me on march 20th at 7pm est (((link in bio))) for my next free webinar where we will discuss not only teaching self-love to our children, but the effects of the generation gap also. one more thing, i'll share my own story of childhood trauma and how i've overcome. everyone who attends will receive a copy of my 30 day breaking toxic cycles journal for free! sign up and share this link with others!!!!!
*********
i can't wait to grow and elevate with you!!!!!!

text:
a 17 years old teenage girl from northwestern china has created shock waves by publicly accusing a schoolteacher of four years of rape, physical abuse and blackmail.

the girl, now 17, told the city and youth channel of shaanxi television on wednesday that the teacher at chenggu county no 4 middle school in shaanxi province forced her into a sexual relationship and threatened her with violence if she spoke about the attacks. "all girls who have come forward in an environment with such a patchy rule of law and pressure from the public are brave," another said.

students at schools and colleges began to speak out last year in the wake of the international #metoo movement and a national campaign against sexual harassment that spread across schools and college campuses.

a year ago, luo qianqian, a former student at beihang university in beijing, alleged that she and at least five other women had been sexually harassed by one of their professors. the professor was fired after an inquiry found his behaviour "was a breach of administrative discipline and the norms of being a teacher". #saynotoviolence#nomore#news#china#asia

text:
one of vancouver's brightest - energy, pizz-azz, smiles and conviction - we are delighted to welcome sheri rowe to this year's women's day programming in vancouver. .
.
sheri rowe has worked in the entertainment industry for nearly 10 years, most recently as producer for jfl northwest - vancouver’s just for laughs festival. sheri is a driven and resourceful event production professional, known for her abilities to think creatively, her dynamic skill set, and her commitment to every project. 
among her live event production achievements are: site operations with the opening and closing ceremonies of the sochi olympic games, artist experience curation and management with premiere festivals across canada, touring emcee with a national tour and live weekly broadcast, and cross functional roles with the largest events within bc.  sheri has executed on all these events through her expertise in project management, production coordination, event logistics, and client & sponsor management. .
.
sheri will be a speaker on monday and she'll be sweating along side all of us at the "weekend rituals" program on march 9 & 10. join us for whole week!
. .
the well beings & weekend rituals (march 4, 9 & 10)
https://iwd2019vancouver.eventbrite.ca or the link in @minibarcanada’s profile.

among her live event production achievements are: site operations with the opening and closing ceremonies of the sochi olympic games, artist experience curation and management with premiere festivals across canada, touring emcee with a national tour and live weekly broadcast, and cross functional roles with the largest events within bc.  sheri has executed on all these events through her expertise in project management, production coordination, event logistics, and client & sponsor management. .
.
sheri will be a speaker on monday and she'll be sweating along side all of us at the "weekend rituals" program on march 9 & 10. join us for whole week!
. .
the well beings & weekend rituals (march 4, 9 & 10)

text:
just me. floating in an ocean. contemplating the fuck out of existence. 
kind of wishing i will sink down into its depths and dissappear. 
vanish. 
maybe turn into a mermaid. 
full of magic. 
cast hexes on all meat eating motherfuckers. 
sorry. 
was that harsh? 
judgemental? 
do i have the energy to give a fuck if it is? 
i mean, i piss you off but you pay people to destroy forests,  to farm and murder animals for no good reason. 
so who should be offended really? 
still you? no. 
maybe the planet. 
she is the only one to be offended really.
she creates this beautiful species, a human race full of spiritual potential. and we fuck it all up by worshipping power, money, and control. 
i would be dissapointed for sure. 
mother earth does not deal with dissapointment. she has no expectations.  that is my issue. 
i expect too much. 
i expect people to give a fuck. 
and you don't. 
my fault. 
expectations. 
my lack of understanding. 
i don't understand. 
at all. help me.

why do you eat animals? or steal their milk? or keep them locked in cages to steal their menstruation? 
i am yet to find a reason that makes sense.
enlighten me. please. 
#veganrant #sorrynotsorry #apparentlyimhavingaday.
.
thank you to those who are conscious consumers. those who try. the non vegans who still choose vegan options. the reduceterians. the plant based. the people who give a fuck. thank you for that too. xx
.
.
#veganbitch #vegansofig #vegansism #stopthesuffering #meatismurder #dairyisrape #fuck #aloneandconfused #mentalhealthissues #depressedbythisworld #ignorant #metoo
📷 @pablo.narayana

text:
"a deeper sense of being" series 32 of 44. 
become a patron and get exclusive access to poetry videos for just $5/month!

www.patreon.com/unjuliwrites

a deeper sense of being

her mouth speaks rainbows
and her lips
have the faint trace
of humility and grace. 
her hair is
waves of austerity
rooted in
the consciousness 
of her intricate mind. 
delve deeply 
into her soul
and you will find
a brave lion
triumphantly basking
in the aftermath
of a chase
that she has 
won fairly. 
she is there. 
right there
where she belongs. 
freedom is
her middle name
and this is her version 
of the game
of life. 
ask her twice
why she still
delicately 
plants seeds 
into buckets of forgiveness 
and she will tell you
that there is
an abundance of hope
which never dies. 
fortune lays around
her bare feet
and her toes
greet each new step
with a healthy dose
of mindful compassion. 
there is less stress
then there ever has been,
since the birth
of her new way of living
conquered 
the pent-up energy
which was keeping her down. 
you might be astounded
to discover
that her heart doesn't beat;
it pounds ferociously 
because her will
is so strong
it can shatter 
any unwelcome thought
with the sleight
of a finger. 
imagine what she can do
with her hands. 
look into her
candlelit eyes
and you will see
a version of yourself
you never thought
you'd see:
a tree so dense 
that rain 
never reaches the ground
with roots tucked 
under folds of 
cement barriers
reaching all the way
to middle-earth.

point to her
curvy lines 
and you will find
a sequence
of verses
which soothes minds
with the ease
of a simple
raindrop. 
she is a forest
with fires and rivers
cascading into
the quiver of her
steadfast lower lip. [...to be continued] © anjuli nunn 2018

rooted in
the consciousness 
of her intricate mind. 
delve deeply 
into her soul
and you will find
a brave lion
triumphantly basking
in the aftermath
of a chase
that she has 
won fairly. 
she is there. 
right there
where she belongs. 
freedom is
her middle name
and this is her version 
of the game
of life. 
ask her twice
why she still
delicately 
plants seeds 
into buckets of forgiveness 
and she will tell you
that there is
an abundance of hope
which never dies. 
foune lays around
her bare feet
and her toes
greet each new step
with a healthy dose
of mindful compassion. 
there is less stress
then there ever has been,
since the bih
of her new way of living
conquered 
the pent-up energy
which was keeping her down. 
you might be astounded
to discover
that her hea does not beat;
it pounds ferociously 
because her will
is so strong
it can shatter 
any unwelcome thought
with the sleight
of a finger. 
imagine what she can do
with her hands. 
look into her
candlelit eyes
and you will see
a version of yourself
you never thought
you'd see:
a tree so dense 
that rain 
never reaches the ground
with roots tucked 
under folds of 
cement barriers
reaching all the way
to middle-eah.

point to her
curvy lines 
and you will find
a sequence
of verses
which soothes minds
with the ease
of a simple
raindrop. 
she is a forest
with fires and rivers
cascading into
the quiver of her
steadfast lower lip. [...to be continued] © anjuli nunn 2018

text:
my favorite time of the day. sitting down and asking my heart what i need. what oils call out to me? this bag goes everywhere with me. and as i mentioned in a previous post from today, it has about 18 roller blends — roller tops on my faves, or blends i created myself.
⠀⠀
tonight, these three call to me. sacred mountain, release and a blend i call self love (acceptance, abundance & joy) ✨💓🌸 release and i have a wonderful, thriving relationship. last summer i remember watching a movie with my partner travis and one of our friends. and it reminded me of the toxic relationship i ran away from a few months ago. the manipulation, the blame, shame and abuse.
⠀⠀
release was created for exactly that purpose. to let go of anger and trauma, deep emotions that are housed in the memory center of the liver. did you know that our body hangs into trauma at a cellular level?! our body hangs onto memories far longer than our mind!
⠀⠀
i roll release over my liver (underneath the right breast) to help support my emotions. the forgiveness i’ve been able to give to others and to myself — i never would have thought i could get to this point of healing. and a lot of that process has to do with oils to help support.
⠀⠀
oils don’t heal or cure anything, babes. they are plant juices that touch our bodies in such an intimate and personal way. but they sure as goodness make like a whole lot easier and lovely ✨🌸💛
⠀⠀
this was a liiiiiittle more deep, but authenticity is what i’m about. if we’re gonna lift each other up, it’s gotta be in the serious stuff, too. you are always welcome on my little corner of instagram — @bethany_bourgoin & @vibrantheartessentials. because you are so stinkin’ worthy, girl 💓🌻
⠀⠀

text:
kaki saya yang pendek seringkali menyulitkan saya menjangkau tempat-tempat yang saya inginkan. mau nonton pawai, mau nonton konser, mau lihat artis lewat di tengah kerumunan, harus jinjit. itu pun belum tentu sukses.
.
tapi kaki saya yang pendek ini sering mengingatkan saya akan keterbatasan saya dan betapa saya ini bukan apa-apa tanpa mereka-mereka yang berada di sekitar saya untuk membantu saya.
.
dan kalau “a story of wounds” (jangan bosen-bosen denger ini di temlen saya ya, netijen) bakal sampai jogja di akhir bulan maret ini, sudah jelas karena banyak sekali dukungan dari orang-orang di sekitar kami. mereka yang kelihatan maupun yang enggak kelihatan. mereka adalah orang-orang yang membantu kaki-kaki pendek seperti kaki saya ini untuk melangkah maju dan naik ke tempat yang lebih tinggi. seperti kawan saya @puspitadesi_ yang bisa-bisa aja ambil foto yang sedang ‘krengkangan’ ini dengan apik.
.
sulit bukan berarti tidak bisa. tetap doakan dan dukung kami, kawan-kawan, karena tanpa kalian, kaki-kaki pendek ini tidak akan berjalan lebih jauh dan tidak akan melompat lebih tinggi.
.
“a story of wounds”
touring production 
march 23, 2019
auditorium driyarkara
sanata dharma university
yogyakarta
.
save your seat: bit.ly/asow2019_yk
.

text:
yesterday, on february 28th, the homewood academic council decided to revoke professor juan obarrio’s tenure and terminate his employment with johns hopkins university. 
anyone acquainted with american academia knows how historic this decision is. for far too long, we have seen survivors of sexual violence on and off campuses see their attackers remain in positions of power, maintain their credibility and continue to prey upon vulnerable people. but that just changed. the academic council, with pressure from every single one of you who held them accountable, just set a precedent that can provide hope for survivors everywhere. 
there is still a long way for johns hopkins to go. many of the demands from our petition are yet to be met. we know that sexual violence on this campus is systemic, institutionalized, covered up and ignored. we know the university needs to change its procedures of investigation, drastically and as soon as possible. we know it has made mistakes that simply cannot be reversed. but this is a momentous and encouraging first step. the jhtoo movement teaches us that collective action, breaking institutional silence, intersectional solidarity, and the care of our peers can indeed change things for the better. 
with your participation in our protest, our petition, our letter-writing campaign and our social media outreach, we  collectively made the seemingly impossible, possible. 
the academic council’s decision needs to be approved by the provost, the president and the board of trustees. professor obarrio can still appeal this decision. we are watching all these stakeholders, to make sure that this process reaches its just conclusion. we really are almost there. once it does reach its conclusion, this will be the first time in the history of jhu’s homewood campus that a professor’s tenure is revoked. 
for everyone still fighting out there - we will and we must keep fighting together. it hasn’t been easy, and every step of the way we faced people who dissuaded us from speaking out and demoralized us. but more importantly, we kept going because of the people who did believe in us. thank you to our countless supporters and fellow activists.

text:
incredible statement and #oscars2019 winning doco. can’t wait to see it on @netflix . 
when i asked my indian brother-in-law to help me start a sanitary pad making enterprise i understood the shame and stigma attached & why he said no. .
i had a chance to help my #kerala family set up a production developed by the phenomenal “pad man” arunachalam muruganantham, a social activist from tamil nadu, but wasn’t meant to be.

the story of mr muruganantham is amazing; welder by trade, he set about creating affordable sanitary towels after discovering that his wife, shanthi, had been using dirty rags during her periods, and was named one of @time 100 most influential people. .
#socialactivism #womensmovement and the #metoo  movements are all playing incredible roles in giving girls and women’s voices in india, and on behalf of my neice, sister-in-law and mother-in-law i want you to know that it does reach them and it is helping to create positive change.  #thankyou .
.
#womenempowerment #womensupportingwomen #womeninspiringwomen #activism #modernslavery #womenentrepreneurs #entrepreneur #girlstothefront #girlpower

text:
in no particular order, over the span of five months, these are some of the red flags.
•child went from being very affectionate, would even be in tears if they forgot to give a hug and a kiss goodbye to someone to seemingly out of nowhere, not wanting to say goodbye, accepting hugs, would tell me i could hold her elbow if crossing the road.
•child no longer allowed assistance during bath and after in cleaning/drying privates (always an upset around it).
•would make comments like, “i don’t get sad or cry. if i’m going to, i just hold my breath and then i don’t cry.”
•a friend of my husbands came over and once he left, child asked what his privates looked like.
•sleep was a massive issue. slept in our bed for a few months, then made a little bed on the floor in case child felt they needed to come in.
•became fearful of doors being closed and would yell out not to lock it (never did this). child would frantically run around home ensuring all doors were open.
•child became ocd, a stutter started, and typical 3 yo tantrums turned into 45min meltdowns where child would throw books and shoes and try to hurt us. even with distance between us, child would yell, “let go of me. don’t touch me.”
•child on own accord decided to stop sleepovers
•after one sleepover, i picked up and once home, found child in tears in car seat. child said, “i need to tell a grownup something. i need to talk to you and daddy.” once in our home, held, and calmed down, child was acting very silly and baby like and said they missed their friend and wanted to play with them.
•when “said” family member was over after a sleepover or play date, that person would constantly go into detail about all that they did and would always look for agreement from my child, “we did x, right? right?”
•cameras at said family members home always seemed to have issues. during day play dates, they seemed to work, but sleepovers, when i would use the app to check my phone the cameras never worked. *i truly hope that this can help even just one person.

text: alright. so here’s the thing. when all this crazy stuff happened in ca with the new labor law, i kinda freaked. like, everyone did. there’s pros and cons to this new law for us strippers. a very large con is that strip clubs are stealing wages. they expect you to make them money before you’re able to receive your wages. clubs are saying now even as employees that we have to make $100-$150  before we even see any money handed to us. to break this down to my non-industry peeps or those in bands, it’s like a “pay to play” scenario. (pay the venue to play the venue and now you’ve died from exposure) got it? rad. we call that wage theft. the pros of this is include that now that we are considered employees, we can strike and unionize to create better working conditions for ourselves because we don’t have a choice. we’re employees now. we have dealt with sexual harassment from management & other non-dancing club workers, racism, homophobia, ageism & ableism for far too long. this is literally our time to strike and band together to help each other. also, founders of the #metoo movement are backing the founders of @soldiers.of.pole who are lawyered up and ready to go to start this industry change for the better. that should tell you something. also, stop fucking listening to club owners about this stuff. they aren’t strippers-we are. talk amongst the ones living it. #castripperstrike

text:
“multiplicity of the mind” theory informs the concept of having an “inner child” as a “part” within us. our inner-child part comes forward when needed/necessary! observe this child within you with lots of compassion, kindness, and acceptance...like all other “parts” within, your inner child just wants to be fully seen, recognized, and accepted .
.
.
.

text: how shame works ..... the saying “misery loves company” is so true when it comes to sexual abuse and the minds of those who abuse. light will always attract darkness and the light of young children is precisely what is so attractive to those who abuse; the innocence, the vulnerability and the beauty and simplicity of how children see the world.  this light of young children, which i believe is the light of their soul, is exactly what is fractured when sexual abuse occurs.  the child is drawn into a very dark world and made to feel as though they too, are part of that world. that somehow, this darkness is part of them. it is this darkness, where the feeling of shame associated with sexual abuse originates.  however, this darkness does not belong to the child, rather it is the world of the abuser.  for those who struggle with shame associated with abuse, please remember this. it is not your darkness, it does not belong to you, it was something you were introduced to.  nothing gets healed in the dark.  nothing.  remember your light. ❤️⭐️♥️ #sexualabuse #metoo #metoomovement #shame #healing #divinefeminine #divinemasculine #divine #childadvocate #parenting #educatingkids #soul
name: Karen Keavy

text:
“the feminist five are li maizi (li tingting), wei tingting, zheng churan, wu rongrong, and wang man, a group of women’s rights activist that rose to international prominence in 2015 after being criminally detained for planning a public sexual harassment awareness campaign. […] the five remained in detention for 37 days, and were released on bail on april 13, two days after u.s. secretary of state john kerry issued a call for their freedom. they were released under qǔbǎo hòushěn (取保候审), meaning that they would be subject to intense surveillance, restrictions, and further investigation for up to one year.” ___

under chinese government’s restriction of internet and activist freedom, the feminist five are perceived as radical in their attempts to bring attention to sexual harassment and the #metoo movement, a hashtag that is consistently censored. the feminist five and other grassroots activists skirts mass censorship by utilizing the words #ricebunny” (#米兔 or #🍚🐰), pronounced as “mi tu”. in a world where feminism is viewed through a western lens, it is imperative to give voices and praises to those participating in activism under regimes and rulings that deny freedom of political dissent and oppress and marginalize women and lgbtq+ communities.

the initial paragraph was retrieved from a people of the week article for china digital times, a news site that reports on “news items which are blocked, deleted or suppressed by china's state censors.” (wiki) the image used of the feminist five was retrieved from a cnn article, “fighting for their rights landed these young chinese feminists in jail.” li maizi’s quote was retrieved from her guardian op-ed article, “i went to jail for handing out stickers in china.”

text:
women get falsely accused too. and we aren’t crying about it. we lawyer up and sue. .
.
yelp allows an abusive loophole. boycott yelp until they stop the manipulative business tactics that parallel the actual domestic violence. yelp violates their own rules by keeping up a review from someone who never received services, if you don’t pay them (extortion). i never even created this listing. it was created by a business in encintas i worked for long ago. so he’s risking 2 lawsuits if he doesn’t delete the fabricated review. .
.
he was not a client, but rather a man i briefly dated until my intuition led me to reach out to a woman.. who confirmed she was his girlfriend. then another. we all gathered together to protect the health and safety of the other women. i am a fierce advocate for women. .
.
when he lost his place to live, his modeling agency, & 5+ women in 1 week, he became enraged & violent. he threatened my safety and threatened my business (some of the women were financially supporting him). this man is a hollywood actor with some initial fleeting success and these women are amazingly beautiful, strong, successful, intelligent, talented, heart-centered women. .
.
anyone is susceptible to domestic violence. no one is immune. and you are not to be blamed for his morals and bad behavior, but you are responsible to leave as soon as he shows you who he is. these types don’t change. burn that bridge. .
.
this wasn’t my only experience with the #toxicmasculine (in both women and men) in the last few years. it’s only made me stronger and faster. i was at the courthouse today. i’m completely comfortable with law suits after the last 5 yrs. .
.
these experiences have given me a unique perspective to support my clients who are navigating this type of abuse. especially women. where i went wrong 5 yrs ago was not seeking a supportive group of women who have been through it. a group of empowered women is the strongest force on the planet. .
.
sisters, don’t get sucked into the programming that you should be jealous and suspicious of other women. that’s patriarchy: it divides, isolates, & conquers. #togetherwearestronger #boycott #yelp #integrity

text: empress taytu betul was a powerful player in preventing ethiopia from being colonized by italy. because her achievement was unexpected, taytu was never credited for helping ethiopia not be colonized. according to the royal historian, the emperor always consulted her before making any radical decisions. being patriotic and believing in her country, empress taytu encouraged her husband to declare war against italy at the battle of adwa. unlike other women, empress taytu helped the downfall of italy at adwa by being a military strategist, fighting at the frontline, and motivating men against retreat. empress tatyu also encouraged women to be involved by inviting them to fight at adwa and become nurses for wounded soldiers. as ethiopian, we are inspired to have an empress who advocated and practiced gender representation. although the time empress lived was more difficult for women, she didn’t allow an obstacle to prevent women from fighting at adwa. let us follow taytu’s footsteps and become involved in #metooethiopia to help ethiopian. let us be brave like empress taytu and work together to prove assault is a crime, not a culture.  #metooethiopa #grlpwr  #ethiopia #africa #metoo #adwa #womenhistory  # #blackhistory #habeshahistory

text_retweet:
i’m working on a really cool project with my good friend, shannon (@cannabisforbreakfast) to showcase the stories of trauma and how women are healing with cannabis. i love being behind the scenes to pull it all together. go follow @this_is_jane_doc to see how we hope to impact the world. . . . . . #repost @this_is_jane_doc with @get_repost
・・・
to kickoff women’s herstory month we’re excited to announce the first #thisisjane storytellers series! 
featuring 5 #womxn from diverse backgrounds, each with an equally courageous story to tell, #thisisjane is bound to be an insightful journey into the lives of everyday womxn negotiating an array of trauma(s) with the help of plant medicine. ⠀
⠀
what occurred at the first event this week speaks to the power in unapologetic womxn facing extreme circumstances with our dear friend, jane, and why this body of work needs to be created.
⠀
our why: ⠀
the silence surrounding violence against womxn needs to end. we believe that cannabis can be both a bridge and a vessel in ending that silence. ⠀
⠀
she helps the sexual-assault survivor find her words. she helps the little girl who lost her mom at 10, negotiate a lonely and obsessive world into her thirties. she helped the violent crime survivor leave her house again. ⠀
⠀
so we tell our stories not only in homage to our personal & collective healing via plant medicine, but also to end the stigma against discussing the horrific things that happen to womxn all over this world every day. ⠀
⠀
would you share yours? ⠀
⠀
everyday for the next 2 weeks we will be posting a different jane’s trauma & healing anecdote to support the mission of this project.⠀
⠀
in gratitude,⠀
#tijcrew ⠀
⠀
-stay tuned! ⠀
⠀

・・・
🔥 hello 🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥 announcement 🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥 may 2019 🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥 “the firebrand new york times columnist and bestselling author of shrill provides a brilliant and incisive look at how patriarchy, intolerance, and misogyny have conquered not just politics but american culture itself. 
what do adam sandler, donald trump, and south park have in common? why are myths like “reverse sexism” and “political correctness” so seductive? and why do movie classics of yore, from sixteen candles to revenge of the nerds, make rape look like so much silly fun? with lindy west’s signature wit and in her uniquely incendiary voice, the witches are coming lays out a grand theory of america that explains why trump’s election was, in many ways, a foregone conclusion. 
as west reveals through fascinating journeys across the landscapes of pop culture, the lies that fostered the catastrophic resentment that boiled over in the 2016 presidential race did not spring from a vacuum. they have in fact been woven into america’s dna, cultivated by generations of mediocre white men and fed to the masses with such fury that we have become unable to recognize them as lies at all. 
whether it be the notion overheard since the earliest moments of the #metoo movement that feminism has gone too far or the insistence that holding someone accountable for his actions amounts to a “witch hunt,” the witches are coming exposes the lies that many have chosen to believe and the often unexpected figures who have furthered them. along the way, it unravels the tightening link between culture and politics, identifying in the memes, music, and movies we’ve loved the seeds of the neoreactionary movement now surging through the nation. 
sprawling, funny, scorching, and illuminating, the witches are coming shows west at the top of her intellectual and comic powers. as much a celebration of america's potential as a condemnation of our failures, some will call it a witch hunt. to which west would reply, so be it: “i'm a witch and i'm hunting you.””

text:
ask #whomademyclothes? ⠀
⠀
it’s a simple question but a hard one to answer - and not many brands can tell you. but since fashion revolution started five years ago, more and more brands are publishing information about where their clothes are made. there’s still a long way to go, so join our collective voice during fashion revolution week april 23-29th to ask for change. this will be the month of our new product launch and we can’t wait to show our labels! we feature new tees offered in our freedom box 📦. all are made by hand and signed by their maker. we think that’s something to celebrate! you will also find handwoven accessories and of course our new leather bags! ⠀
⠀
every garment and artisan worker who makes our accessories, bags and tees are loved, seen, heard, paid properly and working in safe conditions. learn more in april - we hope you stop back. ⠀
⠀
illustration by @shwetamalhotra via  @fash_rev⠀
⠀

text_retweet: this is one of the many reasons i jumped on board with @beautycounter : being part of the african american community is something i will always be proud of, but the products specialized for us are horrible. i tried quite a few of them before switching to beautycounter and they all made my skin worse and pushed me deeper into confusion. we don’t take the time to fully do the research on what we use daily and i understand that because we’re all busy, but now that i have joined i want to be that bridge for my community and all communities to get cleaner, safer products in the hands of everyone!! #africanamerican #cleanbeauty #safer #cleaner #beautycounter #community #consultant #march #besafe #beclean #thistimeitspersonal #everyone #counterman #love #instagood #beautiful #happy #followme #like4like #style #me #smile #repost #anazing #beauty #motavation #blackbeauty #metoo

text:
not a vinyl post: unapologetically. 
i'm officially done with @oprah and any form of support to her and her platform to include her network @owntv (and yes, i will miss greenleaf and queen sugar). oprah we will make sure that your friend #harveyweinsteins trial and documentary of rape and sexual abuse get allll the coverage it deserves. @therealmoworldwide you were right about oprah.  being a @michaeljackson fan can be such a burden at times, but unlike casual listeners,  when shit hits the fan, we diehards research to determine the validity of things and we are everywhere and we are not all wackjobs! no one likes facts anymore. all it takes are accusations, no one checks for motives or credibility anymore. i'm starting to wonder what's the true purpose for having a trial in  the justice system if we now live in a time where we are making verdicts to suit how we feel! i never thought i'd say this, but i am so glad that michael is dead because if he were alive, the amount of humanity he received in death would be just as sketchy as it was in life and with the #metoo cult he'd be tried again and facts would not even matter. #michaeljacksonfans chin up, heads up.. to those who don't get us, just replace the name michael jackson with your favorite sports team, superbowl champ, beatmaker, grade of marijuana,  food....etc  now you get it. #michaeljackson #mjinnocent #agenda #greed #hypocrisy #mjfam #liesrunsprintsbutthetruthrunsmarathons
name: 𝗝𝗮𝘀𝗼𝗻

text:
i've been feeling sad. this voice in my head is annoying and asks: why? 
then, it takes my answer, squishes it into a box titled "reasons sadness doesn't count" and says, stop feeling sorry for yourself. 
can anyone relate? ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
that voice is rude. that voice is wrong. that voice wants to fix and not understand. that voice wants pain to go away and cannot handle emotions. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
the higher voice to that statement doesn't ask why. 
it asks "how can i help?", "do you need to be heard or seen or believed or cuddled or all of it?" ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
the higher voice says, "thanks for telling me. i'm here for you." ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
the higher voice reminds me that sadness is an emotion. i am allowed and invited to feel all my emotions. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
that feeling sad and feeling sorry are completely different things. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
that feeling sad doesn't mean i'm not grateful, or in alignment, or that i have done something wrong. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
the higher voice is the one i am listening to. that is compassion. that is love.  #selfcare #selfcarestrategies #selfcareforthesoul #love #care  #livelaughlove #selfcareisntselfish #selflove #compassion #metoo #mefirst #selfcompassion @prilaga  #selfcarecoach #selfcareisntselfish #selfcareeveryday #sadness  #selfcareisnotselfish  #selfcareday #selfcaretips  #emotions #selfcarelove #selfcaresis  #selfcareroutine #selfcareissacred  #selfcareaccount #selfcarefirst #selfcarematters #selfcaretime

text:
________________________________________я  всех  прощаю,  кто  меня  обидел,
кто  мою  душу  ревностью  терзал,
тех,  кто  меня,  быть  может,  ненавидел,
и  кто  проклятья  вслед  мне  посылал.

я  тех  прощаю,  кто  меня  не  понял,
кто  не  услышал  крик  моей  души,
кто  не  увидел  мир  в  моих  ладонях,
кто  над  любовью  скорый  суд  вершил.

я  тех  прощаю,  кто  не  смог  быть  рядом,
когда  мне  в  жизни  было  тяжело,
кто  мне  желал  изведать  муки  ада,
кто  на  моём  пути  посеял  зло.

я  всем  прощаю  зависть  и  обманы,
предательство,  и  ложь,  и  клевету,
кто  сыпал  соль  на  ноющие  раны,
кто  в  пыль  развеял  сладкую  мечту.

я  всех  прощаю,  кто  был  равнодушен
к  моему  горю  и  к  моим  слезам.
спокойной  ночи  им -  мой  мир  разрушен.
но  сказано: "отмщенье  мне,  и  аз  воздам!" любовь вакуленко

text:
don’t forget to tune into omni tv tonight for our weekly segment from 8-8:30pm!
.
tonights segment is dedicated to our annual special event, call the shots: female power through film taking place on march 8th, in honour of the celebration of international women’s day!
.
what better way to celebrate international women’s day than a panel discussion led by phenomenal women who have made their mark in the cinema industry, followed by the screening of the feature film, nome di donna (the name of a woman), at the tiff bell lightbox
.
in the era of #metoo and #timesup, and a renewed awareness of the dignity of women in the face of subversive harassment and discrimination, giordana's film arrives as a manifesto of rebellion, with its protagonist brought to life by cristiana capotondi, a heroine who dares to break the wall of silence that surrounds her, whatever the cost, to unmask her lecherous boss
.
the tickets for the event are $13. women 30 and under will receive their ticket for free
.
vaughan: march 7th @cinemascineplex 
reception: 6:30pm
screening: 8pm
.
toronto: march 8th
reception: 7pm @orchid.nightclub 
panel: 9pm
film: 9:30pm @tiff_net
.
.
.
.
.

text:
✧ flashbacks: part 5 ✧ in the final installment of our series on flashbacks - though certainly not the last time we'll educate on them or offer coping strategies to get through - we'll be tackling a few ways to heal body memories, physical pain, and/or the mental anguish brought on by flashbacks. here, we take you through, step by step, healing pool and healing light imagery, as well as introduce a few other imagery techniques. these tools are especially helpful in easing stubborn body memories, alleviating pain from chronic illnesses (that are often exacerbated by trauma symptoms), relaxing stress and tension in the body, settling switching headaches, quieting and slowing phrenetic thoughts, and so much more.
.
🏖☀️ link in bio! or head to: beautyafterbruises.org/blog/healingpool ☀️🏖
.
we sincerely hope this very detailed guide can deliver you to a much softer, peaceful state of being -- one where you can breathe easier, feel lighter, and experience a relief you didn't even know was possible. we look forward to hearing your experiences and encourage you to share below some of your favorite personal strategies for coping with body memories as the well as physical and emotion pain brought on by flashbacks. you might have the perfect solution to heal another's pain!
.
💙💚💛
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
true love
love was thick lurking in the winter air
it was your embrace that brought me despair
could you possibly love this one girl only?
or is the whispers i'm hearing from your soul fake, are you plastic or phony?
can't you see that this angel loves you too death? 
she's taken eight of her lives this is her last one left...
stalking you from the dimensions checking from right to left...
what if you choose to hold her and love her now, or wait till your last breath?
will you build her soul up now and then?
she forgets about herself she put herself before everyone else,
until barely anything was left...
will you only hold her now and again?
or do you think of her as just a really good friend?
she's wanted forever to kiss your soft warm lips...
while you pull her in embracing her hip to hip...
when i see the truth i can never be wrong,
her love for you has evolved it's stronger than strong...
loving her in return so that an eternal gift shall be given...
as i see in the near future your family will be making a substantial living...
this was a prayer, she once begged it to be true....
but this angel learned to love herself...
no thanks to you...
her eyes that shine like the stars and the moon...
have been murmured to be awakened soon...
cause even though your love you've found is absolutely true...
you won't remember it until you remember you.

text:
watch the words that slip from your lips...
it's not abuse if you're both trapped in this...
you're just as much at fault don't you see?
if they hit you once you're meant to leave...
the fear is all inside of your lies...
because once they filled your gut with flutterbies
now once you claim assault you've won...
they must leave their lives to be another someone...
not fake their death or commit suicide...
their soul takes a trip you see it in their eyes...
the last time you kissed you felt the goodbye...
as they slipped away to another body to another life.

text:
i should have when i was fifteen
i thought i had something to look forward to
so i listened to the voices when they'd ring
i still have much to do but you're in pain too
no one will even care when you cry
they're all damaged to being dead inside
they lack empathy and subtract sympathy too
they'll watch as someone walks up and kills you
with their cell phones high their moods low 
i'm too young to be responsible so why
was i thrown into being a mom so soon
i'm talking about to all my mom's friends kids
every dark nights end she'd howl at the moon
after hearing the children's fears in their sleep
she'd cry every night her entire legacy
no one even cares that in her heart she bleeds
they think it's all just a big joke about me
no matter who i've trusted heart and soul
their human don't believe me just like will
they think that rape is always remembered
tho i didn't recall it until that early september
i'm never going to heal from this it's here still
always nicer to some other bitch as well
i guess i'm chopped liver throw me in a well
as i put satin lotion on my pale freckled skin.

text:
tell future me.
this shit ain't worth it.
like the sun ain't warm enough.
still parasites around me.
like so am i just deceiving...
how they pretend to give a fuck..
but only care about themselves.
how anger is easier than giving love...
cause they've been alone for so long...
like why is it wrong to not want...
to walk this earth anymore cause they give up
give in go back to being locked up
in employment that's like prison...
thinking you got enough but want more...
say your love is enough...
i've been homeless for you...
all in the name of love you believed my truth.
i'm sorry my head gets confused...
i've been abandoned enough...
but i have serious trust issues.
i just wanted to be a kid again
deep in love...
but this world won't allow it. 
so i fucking give up...
i'll just keep going along...
until my kids are grown up...
i'm tired i just want to get out of this skin
i'd make the perfect wife...
if you'd just love me enough to let me in...
but you don't.
so i'll just do what i'm told like before.
cause i can't live without you in my life.
even if i'm losing my mind...
i just wanted you to be the one on it 
but you're not strong enough...
so fuck this life i'm not living it.
zombie mode wife...
like my ex couldn't get...
tell me you're going to take care of me...
but what i do is never enough...
so fuck it... i'm over it. 
don't give a fuck...

text:
were you honestly molested or raped? cause if you were you don't just forget that stuff, and accusing someone innocent is biligerant... there's so many of those of us, who have literally had to live it. couldn't accuse no one, cause back then no one wanted to listen. school says tell your family tell your mom... but what if they are part of it? we have to live with this stuff... left alone cause someone took our bodies without offering it. i'm 38 years old. i thought i've already rererelived this shit... but over it. but i guess not. a woman who was raped by her husband... she can't just get over that sort of fucked up. so i didn't. just wish i could die today. cause in my head he's in it. fuck my life i want off this rock.

text:
can't we get this over with?
i'm tired of your demons shit 
i might just find someone else
who can deal with it...
stop lying to me in my head
you say you're my protector
tho i keep feeling dead
it's like a harsh reality projector
playing the same shit ahead
the thoughts in my brain
going over and over instead
telling me to leave you
but i'm not that insane
i know if i was to go
you'd regret it immediately
i don't have that time though
can you please work with me?
i'm past the ten years i give
i wanted you the rest of this life
but this isn't the way i need to live
wondering everyday if i'm enough
even though i've given everything
that makes me who i am and what i used to love
i'm not saying that i want to go away
i need you too much but here i'm afraid
i'm naked in front of you tears don't do shit
so i'm going to go numb again
until you start to prove it
you're different and it's all my fault
i was going through some dumb ass shit
i told you you couldn't handle me
i'm scary to be close to i said this
i warned you i'm hard to love
though you said that you got this
i'm damaged so much no one can undo
the only thing that keeps me going...
was you... but you don't want that anymore.
don't say i didn't warn you.
no one my age or close
can do this tough love shit...
you're not equipped.

text:
i'm gonna make you trust me
last one don't trust nothing
believers can't be deceived
deceivers will never ever believe
there's wolves in sheep's clothing
but they act just like you and me
they lie about their wants and needs
slowly bury you until you can't breath
if you can't be alone at all you're not free
you can be alone but without your love
you're going to go into slowly dying
a state of numbness you're never being
just cause you're hurting to mean nothing
the girl is supposed to be the weaker
she needs a man to pick her up n stick her
nail her up against the wall and expect nothing from her
lay her on her back in bed lay kisses all over
sometimes your demons get the best of her
she feels them in your sleep she knows it when you're creeping
but something amazing... she can't feel it if the sex she loves... is the same.
so she's always afraid and waiting...
so it creates a domino thing...
so i'm going to let you go baby.
i need someone stronger by my side.

text:
i gave you the best of my best years,
and through all of the tears,
i don't regret any of my kids,
but i'm tired of what i hear.

cause you lie....
because you lie... cause you lie....
because you lie... you said that i did you wrong,
and for that you are strong...
you tell them i was at fault,
and that you were faithful all along... but you lie...
i know that you lie,
cause you lie...
because you lie.

they think i left without cause,
that i was lying all along...
you said i used you all that time,
but that's cause you were the one,

cause you lied...
because you lie...
cause you lied...
because you lie.

i went through so many problems,
trying to find out what i did wrong,
i thought that giving you all you want,
would make our love so much stronger.

but you lied...
i told you, you'd lie,
because you lied....
because you lie.

you told them i kept you at home...
that i cut you off from your mom,
you said i left without warning,
but you knew when i was gone... cause you lied.
because you lie, 
cause you lied.
because you lie.

so now that we're starting a new year,
i make a promise from now and here...
i won't let you rub me wrong,
i'm not going to let you hurt my feelings...
it's alright though huni, you're an ex for a 
reason... because you lied.
and continue to lie. 
because you lie....
and i'm sorry, but this time... i know that i'm 
right....
cause you.... chose to lie.

text:
i'm sweet
innocent
we'll talk about it
i'm passionate
i get really really loud
all night long
piss me off
or play me a song
on the lower part of my back
or when you stretch off my thong
i know what i want
just don't take unless it gives cause
i ain't chasing i want to be chased for once
i'm not crying wolf
i got so much to offer
just come by n spend it
every single dropping
as my thoughts are shocking
i'm gonna play gift
let you walk by her a whiff
secret garden in the bushes with you
young at heart i remember
the time i walked with you
the woods would have been perfect
but you were a gentle
one... didn't try to take control...
let me mend your heart.
my broken is just harkened
i ain't been deep yet
come give me some love
i wanna fall in
don't need to be romantic
just pin me down
make... run to.

text:
i'm not dilerious 
it's not the sleep i'm missing
it's so hilarious
they think it's just a little something
can't it explain it to "us"
since some haven't earned anything
sacrifice your rem several times
once you miss your day dreams
you'll come apart at the scenes of the crimes
makes them all want to scream
feel like a heart attack in the line
till you're walking in the greens
through meadows of space bound lives
pointed to the stars we got off course beams
french kissed on the moon hours of mine
drifted into la la land with your sublime
write your name in the book of the divine
hear it screening from the roots vibes
purged them up with stomach brine
forget about the rest it's past life
so you learn to cope with the same mines
giving up to give in to your new beginnings
as you fetch through the holes in my life
i'm not sorry it's part of the fire
growing underneath our beings
till it ignites like a thief in the middle of the night.

text:
you're my everything
when i found you
i was nothing
i need you to find my something
i want you by my side
to do everything
we've been waiting for in life
i went to enjoy hot springs
swim in open waters
show you beautiful things
i want your eyes to see
that there's more to life than we
there's wolves and horses
waiting for us to spread our wings
you're my poe
to the allen of my edgar
like a roach calling me family
and removing my velvet choker
your lips brought me back
your hands created my soul
making my skin vibrate
as i began to lose control
i felt like i couldn't live without you
though i've done it so long before
i just wanted to be stronger for you
now i promise you if you met me there...
i'll give you so much more.

text:
all of these tears falling
wasting the previous lives times
worrying over what you lost
instead of what's in your next life
get held down by a neighbor
howdy how ya doin?
they get you distracted
while they be tuning
into things you don't want them to
friends can be amazing
watch who they mistreat
the ones who fear the light
will bring your soul into retreat
them fucking demons
suck up all of your soul
like damage is their mission
find all your broken holes
pouring acid into the pores
leak your insecurities
bleach them out on the floor
bring a mop and a bucket large
they're taking over
it's time to come up sarg...
mistreatment was the design
to remove these broken wires
rotate your human mind
to not think but bend
like we've done with time
the ups the downs
everything in between
the monsters coming out tonight
i swear they don't be mean
they're picking up the missing pieces
of the puzzle we lost long ago
so please sit still
swallow that bitter pill
beg for forgiveness
so you can be part
of the chosen ones.
it's your que.

text:
you ever crush so hard on someone
that you see them in everyone? 
you can be close to them and even with them for a long time...
but you still crush. 
when you're crushing for your love
that means it's real
it never stops
you're already in love
love yourself
and you'll find that love is more than a 4 letter word
it's more than a phrase
don't love anyone like you do you
they will love you equally
when they love themselves
if you don't love yoself
for any reason
whoever you're with
deals with that insecurity
in themselves
if you want to build a strong woman
to help lift up a strong man
and vice versa
you must first
stop loving selfishly
stop loving with jealousy
if you're afraid of losing who you're with
it's not meant to be
no love should make you fear losing them
it's in your own mind
you cause it
so stop it.

text:
where's that smile
you used to make
the one that took mountains
to take all away
absorbed by the energies
to bring you home to me
my soul
i know i've scared you
i know i've lied to you
i know i've hurt you terribly
i'm sorry
i had to break through
so i can finally see me
i see you soul
you're mine no one owns
i share
willingly
i'm waiting for the smile
to return to my eyes
the life that removed lies
i have a disguise
i've found my life
in my own demise
so soul i'll dance with you tonight
we'll find reasons to smile
to bring me back to life...

text: yesterday i turned 28. the girl in this picture wasn’t sure if she would make it to that number. she looked fine, but she was hurting inside. she refused to smile throughout high school because she believed it made her ugly. but looking back maybe she didn’t smile because it made her feel phony. this girl has grown into something she could never imagine. a woman who feels confident and beautiful. this woman is resilient. she knows what internal resources she has and her external ones support her. thank you to the girl in this picture for taking life a day at a time in order for this woman to dream of oceans and mountains without fear.

text:
they turned on me. 
every last one. 
said you were bad for me. 
so instead i run. 
no one can even see...
the tears that still run. 
at night when you're in your sleep?
i just lay here waiting on you, my one...
the things they said...
lies i swear.
i've always been good.
how would you know?
you weren't there.
the nights i slept alone...
before i knew your touch here?
i swear it was my only song...
dancing for you out there. 
the burning in my skin...
brought by the summer sun?
it was meant for you to hear...
the pain emitting from my heart. 
you've gone this long with what you think...
so i'm good on my own. 
your opinion? 
it stinks. 
i'm no fragile being.
for myself i've had to be strong. 
so next time you get to thinking...
about me? 
start worrying about yourself, son...
cause placing blame is one thing....
we're already in love.
here's the messed up thing though... you're still lost in the shuffle some.
so i'm just...
here waiting.

text:
i've been thinking
about how you sped
highway 66 winking
as you passed cars some
you still angry with me?
it's ok i'm not a fan of cleaning...
you're on the way hun
though i feel you sinking
the memories returning some
i tried calling you 
but you had no service
on your cell phone
i tried to call you
inside my mind
so it started ringing
every single time
i'd call your name
in my wake and in my sleep
though you were still deaf
afraid of hurting the real me
you seem to forget
we've done this over and over instead
now bring your pretty little mind
back to my favorite head
i've gone through shit
just to prove i'm worth it
said i'm sorry
but you still don't believe it
you forget yourself
that's why you're so far gone
but baby i swear on the life
of your first born son
i'm your aphrodite.

text:
does she steal a kiss, when you're not thinking of it?
does she touch your chest, and kiss you in various places...
her fingertips tracing your stomach, while she watches you breath,
wondering if you have any clue, that your touch is what she needs...
she doesn't ask for what her body needs, 
hoping her subtle hints, will aim you to please...
her hair drifts softly, over your arm,
while her lips trace soft kisses, 
hoping that she's not causing harm...
she wishes to be desired,
and her needs to be fulfilled,
however, this woman that you love;
won't ask, she refuses to tell...
she wants you to read her mind,
accept her advances, that she's playfully trying...
to get you to notice, 
she needs to feel your love,
in a way that no one else can show her...
by lulling her body to sleep,
with the tenderness and sensuality, 
of your touch...
you need to have intuition.

text:
oh how the weather disguises, the rain that wants to form, 
supplementing tears to clear the skies, 
the cold just freezes, what do we gain?

it melts when warm winds start to change,
however the rain still needs to claim,
the wicked heiress of the spring,
turns to dust with what it seems... to be infernal chaos, with every single breath,
they say that we pollute our air,
though we are responsible for polluting our souls,
no one takes the blame, for all we have to shame,
turning strangers to slit their wrist,
all in political or religious twists,

until you've had a chance to wallow,
in the pity of self we've taken on,
don't judge thy neighbor, on what you may think,
love the sinner, hate the sin,
because your sin is not lesser, you still don't win.

a burden so caught up, in the chest,
you call it love? 
i call it sticking to my senses,
waiting for the rain as it cleanses,
all the things we've said, we've done,
to prove we are unworthy,
of the blessing, called god's son.

text:
oh how the weather disguises, the rain that wants to form, 
supplementing tears to clear the skies, 
the cold just freezes, what do we gain?

it melts when warm winds start to change,
however the rain still needs to claim,
the wicked heiress of the spring,
turns to dust with what it seems... to be infernal chaos, with every single breath,
they say that we pollute our air,
though we are responsible for polluting our souls,
no one takes the blame, for all we have to shame,
turning strangers to slit their wrist,
all in political or religious twists,

until you've had a chance to wallow,
in the pity of self we've taken on,
don't judge thy neighbor, on what you may think,
love the sinner, hate the sin,
because your sin is not lesser, you still don't win.

a burden so caught up, in the chest,
you call it love? 
i call it sticking to my senses,
waiting for the rain as it cleanses,
all the things we've said, we've done,
to prove we are unworthy,
of the blessing, called god's son.

however the rain still needs to claim,
the wicked heiress of the spring,
turns to dust with what it seems... to be infernal chaos, with every single breath,
they say that we pollute our air,
though we are responsible for polluting our souls,
no one takes the blame, for all we have to shame,
turning strangers to slit their wrist,
all in political or religious twists,

until you have had a chance to wallow,
in the pity of self we've taken on,
do not judge thy neighbor, on what you may think,
love the sinner, hate the sin,
because your sin is not lesser, you still do not win.

a burden so caught up, in the chest,
you call it love? 
i call it sticking to my senses,
waiting for the rain as it cleanses,
all the things we've said, we've done,
to prove we are unworthy,
of the blessing, called god's son.

text:
recent reflections on my work as a #feminist artist. now i'm in the fourth year of working on my performance art piece baby paradise. i'm still refining it because i want to make its core truth as clear as a crystall. i  speak to you, you broken kids, in the voice of a lost girl: 
often in my life i've felt like a lost girl or a broken doll. yet i had to be in control, i had to smile, i had to pretend that my body wasn't broken, that i wasn't broken. i had to pretend that patriarchy wasn't bullshit and that the way we as girls grow up and we as women are treated is right. although i could list my own #metoo moments here, i better go on with life, and you better go on with life, too. don't forget to smile. just be as perfect as a barbie doll.

once the trans sex worker i was in a relationship in told me 'i like to be used by the customers'. i looked at the expression on her face, the same she put on to appear attractive to her customers. she had an inflammation on her breasts, she had to see a doctor. at the end i couldn't help but i thought she was as lost as i was. 
baby paradise creates a language of trauma. the trauma of the broken doll, the lost and abused girl and the trafficked sex worker alike – or our trauma as women. baby paradise dissects the wounds we sustain in a society that objectifies women, while tabooing female sexuality and sex work.
repetitive gestures and phrases form the cyclical dramaturgy of the performance. telling the truth about late capitalism: we are constantly buying and selling each other, even if we are lost.

#lostgirl #brokendoll #barbiedoll #feminism #feministart #writing #performanceart #femaleartist #trauma #queerart #sexwork #sexworker #againstpatriarchy #againstcapitalism #lost #postmodern #berlin #trauma #berlinartist #control #power

recent reflections on my work as a #feminist artist. now i am in the fourth year of working on my performance art piece baby paradise. i am still refining it because i want to make its core truth as clear as a crystall. i  speak to you, you broken kids, in the voice of a lost girl: 
often in my life i have felt like a lost girl or a broken doll. yet i had to be in control, i had to smile, i had to pretend that my body wasn't broken, that i wasn't broken. i had to pretend that patriarchy wasn't bullshit and that the way we as girls grow up and we as women are treated is right. although i could list my own #metoo moments here, i better go on with life, and you better go on with life, too. do not forget to smile. just be as perfect as a barbie doll.

once the trans sex worker i was in a relationship in told me 'i like to be used by the customers'. i looked at the expression on her face, the same she put on to appear attractive to her customers. she had an inflammation on her breasts, she had to see a doctor. at the end i couldn't help but i thought she was as lost as i was. 
baby paradise creates a language of trauma. the trauma of the broken doll, the lost and abused girl and the trafficked sex worker alike – or our trauma as women. baby paradise dissects the wounds we sustain in a society that objectifies women, while tabooing female sexuality and sex work.
repetitive gestures and phrases form the cyclical dramaturgy of the performance. telling the truth about late capitalism: we are constantly buying and selling each other, even if we are lost.

text:
it was a floral frenzy of femininity and feminism this morning at facebook’ annual international women’s day event!!
✨✨✨
hugely sumptuous in theme and content. ✨✨✨
with advice ranging from owning your own space, to embracing individuality, to my favourite talk by @elizabday who encourages us to learn from failure in this age of curated perfection and build emotional resilience as a muscle you learn to flex. amen. ✨✨✨
@helenabonhamcarter_offical encouraged us to love the wisdom and confidence that comes with age “we shouldn’t go out to pasture just because we’re older”, and the @thekingdomchoir brought soul sparkle to the room with a dancing, singing, memory of a lifetime finale. ✨✨✨
it was a superb industry event, thought provoking, exquisitely organised and there was even a brave all male panel on ‘being allies’! i’m incredibly grateful to have experienced this morning. thank you @facebook and all presenters. it definitely supercharged the rest of my friday 🙏
.
.
.
.
.

.

"jak mám na svete niečo po sebe zanechať, keď som vždy musel po sebe upratať?" tom hashko
2.3. v @bohemabarofficial bude oslavovať @grfka svojich nedožitých 30 a ja nadsluhujem už 31 rokov preťahovaného humoru. bude to nejaká salto-masérska párty, takže mňa nájdeš v rohu takto čakať na pozdrav. 
chlast mi nenos, bar je môj. otvorili sme si ho z darčekov na osemnástku a dražby oblečenia čo si tam ľudia nechávajú. už sa minuli. kúpou panáku ma podporíš skoro tak, ako keď dáš @divadlodpm 2% zo svojich priznaných daní.
budem tam po mischurovej monodráme. keď bude dlhá ako on, tak už o 20.30.
kocúra neprinesiem. ale tvojho môžem vymastiť.

text:
✊🏾it’s fabulous friday✊🏾 a little history lesson, a little shopping! today is the first day of women’s history month, so we will be posting a fabulous lady everyday in march! #015, tarana burke! in 2006, tarana founded the #metoo movement to raise awareness of sexual abuse, assault and harassment, but it really picked up steam after the weinstein allegations. in 1997, she listened to a 13 year old girl who was sexually abused, and didn’t have a response to help her in that moment. it “sat in her spirit for a long time.” this lead her to start just be inc, to help victims of sexual assault and harassment. according to the associated press, the hashtag #metoo was shared in more than 12 million posts in the first 24 hours. she says her vision of #metoo movement “is part of a collective vision to see the world free of sexual violence.” the bold statement has become on of survival. “i am not ashamed, i am not alone.” and for survivors to say to each other “i see you, i hear you and i understand you and i’m here for you.” tarana knows that feminism is not for the male gaze, and no one could agree more than the lovely ladies at @lafilledo. lingerie is for you!
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
i got this tattoo at the end of 2018. it was empowering, i'd wanted one of these for a long time, but didn't quite know what i wanted it to look like. last year was a rough one, full of pain and change, and therefore also full of growth. 
the reason i got this is because while i have always been taught by my family that women are strong, society as a whole still acts in support of the opposite, often times in passive ways, and with some of the experiences i've lived through, there have been times that i have been scared because i was was a woman, and of color at that. i dealt with sexual harassment at work, while the kavanaugh hearings were happening, i dealth with decades-old wounds that never healed properly, and this tattoo meant -enough, stand proud and tall and use your voice. 
there are three flowers inside. the national peruvian flower, a cantuta, a yellow hibiscus, the hawaiian state flower, and the california poppy, california's state flower. i am a tomboy most of the time, but most of you know, i am also very in touch with my feelings. i love the fact that as women, we are strong but we can show off our gentle, compassion, love and femininity the way we want to express it. from the three cultures, i learned different things about being a woman. 
my peruvian side, had taught me to be a nurturing, caring, loving, matriarch. i was lucky to attend an all girls school that empowered girls to strive for greatness in the classroom and in athletics, and the women and men in my family always challenged me to be the best. 
living my teenage years in southern california gave me a voice. that women will do anything men can do, and surpass them. i truly appreciate the liberal politics of california, with powerful women in the highest political positions, fighting for gender equality. i found my political voice.
hawaii healed me, i arrived with a semi-broken soul. i learned about ho'oponopono, how and why we should care about mother earth (malama 'aina) and i met some amazing women that molded me into the woman i've become today. i met some lifelong ladies that were on the journey with me, who encouraged me to excel and taught me the feeling of sisterhood.

text:
sexual assault awareness month is coming soon! 
speaking out isn't the only way to embrace our voices. wear your advocacy on your sleeve by purchasing our exclusive t-shirt, which proudly proclaims that we believe, support, and stand with survivors. the design also features many amazing hashtags related to anti-sexual violence work, so that anyone who sees your shirt can go online and learn more about the movement. 
we have two colors available (black and grey), and each one is available in either crew neck or v-neck. if grey is more your thing, be sure you order asap. this color is exclusively available during the booster campaign and will not be available at any of our future events.

order today, and have your shirt(s) mailed directly to your door in time for advocacy day and sexual assault awareness month! all sales directly support oaesv’s public policy efforts to make ohio safer and more just. hurry--the campaign closes at midnight on 3/16!

#weareoaesv #believesurvivors #supportsurvivors #standwithsurvivors #metoo

taking time to care for yourself is not selfish. i feel like a lot of times, especially as moms, we are thinking about every other person and every other thing we have to do in a day and we forget about our needs! you need to make time for yourself! taking care of yourself enables you to take care of your littles to the best of your ability! get that workout in! eat your greens! read that book! drink that smoothie! take a bath! make yourself healthy and happy and set that example for your kids — it’s not about me, first; it’s about me, too. .

text: the scars on my head one from a hammer the other from a pan. today i can look at them and smile and say i am no longer a victim. not a victim to the abuse nor to the memory.  all the struggle  all the hurt it's never in vain. i am blessed to be able to go through so much and be able to use it to bless and help others in their journey. this is too all the people who have suffered or suffer from sexual physical mental abuse. no matter what you are loved and worth the best and never let anyone tell you otherwise. you are more than your past and current circumstances.  #wholeselfhealing #loveandforgive #thrive #keepstrivingforbetter #nevergiveup #staystrong #knowyourworth #stillirise #godheals #metoo

text:
made some harsh realisations about a couple of things and i've been quite shocked by realising what being in a miserable abusive relationship can do to someone physically. looking back it was quite shocking

those pictures show me single, a month before my last relationship, during my last relationship and then after, now that im in a healthy happy relationship. 
it quite shocking really, especially when you look at the eyes. the during picture looks like i'm internally screaming for help.

don't be afraid to escape something that's killing you inside, keep fighting and escape the abuse. you can and will be happy again.

#isurvived #metoo #abusesurvivor #spousalabuse #thereislifeafterabuse #happierthanever #youcandoit #strongerthanyouknow

text:
it’s women’s history month! it’s going to be a busy one. it’s also friday so i thought we should use this opportunity to connect with more badass women on insta. ———
first, i would like to encourage you to participate in (and follow) @badassherstory - no better time to share your story and make some art than this month!!! ———-
my #followfriday suggestion is the astounding @vichcraft - her feminist lettering and art is off the chain stitch amazing. she is also just a lovely human - and she has a bird that talks! ——-
your turn. who should we follow and why? ——-
let’s do this month right! ———

text:
happy march savoir!⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
do you ever feel like you want to elevate your circle?👇🏼⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
spring is just around the corner. 20 days to be exact. i don't know about you, but this time of year gives me all the feels. we are so excited to introduce to you our theme for march. this month at savoir we are focusing on: "how to curate your surroundings." ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
more specifically, we are focusing on how to level up and elevate your circles. this topic could not be more kismet, especially with spring approaching. this subject lends a good ear to those who need a little push with how to "spring clean" people.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
this month we will be asking our #savoir circle questions about how changing your circle of support can impact your life and women they would love to meet. be on the lookout for content on how to create a new circle of influence, how to reach out to those people in an authentic way, and how to remove toxicity for your life. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
we’ll be posting those questions & answers through the month!..⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text:
in my recent posts, i have been discussing a vision i received: a patchwork quilt which represented my life and all the selves within it, connected by a single golden thread—the one self that flows through them all. it has delivered a big medicine for me and the healing of a hidden sexual trauma recently uncovered.
🦋
this has been the toughest piece of trauma work i have ever had to do because it impacted my being at a very young age. the memories are foggy, delivered by the confused mind of a little girl who didn’t understand what was happening to her, and they came with the overwhelming emotions of a child— unfiltered and without the defenses of an adult mind. it has been an intensely raw and truly exquisite journey as i walked in both worlds— as the little girl emerging from shadow and as the guardian embracing her into the light.
🦋
this is a common experience among those of us healing trauma— to feel inhabited by the one who experienced it. we can interpret it as a fracture of the self, a split, and seek to override the switch and avoid the “triggers”. but this does not serve one’s healing. we must embrace the little girl, or whomever your recipient was, and re-member her. let her walk through the memories and the healing process with you as her guardian. in this way, not only will she finally be able to heal but you will also garner key insights into how your self reformed in reaction to the trauma— the defenses and offenses placed on her frontline along with all her strategies to avoid the battle all together.
🦋
with you holding space for her, she can make the choice to heal without defense. ‘i see you, i hear you, i feel you, i believe you.’ this is what she needed so long ago, what she likely didn’t get from those around her, and what she was too young or too broken to give to herself. as result, she survived but in a dismembered state until she was completely forgotten. this is the true fracture that needs to be healed—the distance between you and her—and it starts by allowing her to be, once again. embrace her, embody her, empower her. reweave her into your patchwork quilt until you are completely integrated once again— the golden thread.
name: Rebecca Haywood
