this has been the toughest piece of trauma work i have ever had to do because it impacted my being at a very young age. the memories are foggy, delivered by the confused mind of a little girl who didn’t understand what was happening to her, and they came with the overwhelming emotions of a child— unfiltered and without the defenses of an adult mind. it has been an intensely raw and truly exquisite journey as i walked in both worlds— as the little girl emerging from shadow and as the guardian embracing her into the light.
🦋
this is a common experience among those of us healing trauma— to feel inhabited by the one who experienced it. we can interpret it as a fracture of the self, a split, and seek to override the switch and avoid the “triggers”. but this does not serve one’s healing. we must embrace the little girl, or whomever your recipient was, and re-member her. let her walk through the memories and the healing process with you as her guardian. in this way, not only will she finally be able to heal but you will also garner key insights into how your self reformed in reaction to the trauma— the defenses and offenses placed on her frontline along with all her strategies to avoid the battle all together.
🦋
with you holding space for her, she can make the choice to heal without defense. ‘i see you, i hear you, i feel you, i believe you.’ this is what she needed so long ago, what she likely didn’t get from those around her, and what she was too young or too broken to give to herself. as result, she survived but in a dismembered state until she was completely forgotten. this is the true fracture that needs to be healed—the distance between you and her—and it stas by allowing her to be, once again. embrace her, embody her, empower her. reweave her into your patchwork quilt until you are completely integrated once again— the golden thread.

text:
own your story. that can be easier said than done. as a survivor, your story probably has a lot of tears, scars, ptsd, triggers and self doubt. echoes of abuse radiate years after the abuse stops. your thoughts and emotions still react to those echoes as if it’s still happening. 
far too often, we try to hid from it all. stuff it down. pretend it doesn’t exist. unfortunately, it can fester and grow inside until it can be held back no longer. the only way to be set free is to willingly let it go. to shine light on the darkness. which can be scary. almost as scary as the abuse itself. 
but what the fear inside your head doesn’t show you, is the ability to connect with other people through your story. it doesn’t tell you of the freedom it will give you to stand up and declare that you won’t be held down any longer. or the surprising amount of people who have similar experiences as you, that will reach out and thank you for letting them know that they aren’t alone. 
finding your tribe of people that understand your struggles and can be there to support each other, is truly priceless. you are worthy of love. you are worthy of support. sharing your story helps you have that.  abuse does not have to hide in silence any longer! you have a voice- it’s ok to use it! 
#survivor, #abuse, #sexualassault, #strength, #metoo, #ownyourstory, #ptsd, #domesticviolence, #connect, #freedom, #selfdefense, #tribe, #support, #silence, #voice

text:
@alisonsudol x @ilfautmagazine
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
in 2017, you released “enough honey,” your debut single under your own name. what influenced your decision in timing to release the single after nearly five years since the last album release (pines) as a fine frenzy? 
it was completely emotionally driven, as we really didn’t have the infrastructure up and running yet to support it; i just had to get it out. it was right after the stories around harvey weinstein came out, the early days of the #metoo movement, and i had just shared my own story live on instagram. i was fired up and inspired, and it seemed like the right time to put the song out into the world.

it was a long time before the rest of the music was ready to come out, and the ep that enough honey is on (moonlite) won’t be out until early spring, but i don’t really mind that. it’s part of why we started our own company, so we can be light on our feet and follow our instincts. ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

ushering in a new wave of feminism, tarana burke started the #metoo movement back in 2006, more than a decade before it was heard around the world. an inspiring leader for victims of sexual assault and harassment, burke's work has allowed hundreds of thousands of women across the globe to speak up about their own sexual assault experiences, and helped open the floodgates for hollywood's time's up movement. burke's "me too" concept created a safe space for women to speak up and fight back against sexual misconduct and marked a new chapter in the future of feminism.

from experiencing assault in dark corridors of the er, to feeling like “the operating room is the locker room,” women in healthcare are now speaking out and demanding safe, equitable workplaces. “i thought, well if it happens in their industry, and they’re uniting with farmworkers and all these other industries… i thought it was weird that these conversations were happening in parallel but not joined,” jessi gold, md, ms, tells @inlauraswords. so she sent a tweet to @timesupnow saying, hey, there are some women doctors i think you need to talk to. and the rest is soon to be history, as time’s up healthcare officially launches on march 1. more on how @timesuphc is taking on sexism in doctors’ offices and hospitals at the link in bio. #timesuphc

text:
omdat: iedereen kent wel iemand kent die ongevoelig is en gevoeligheid afstraft of labelt.

de verrijkende relatie (niet alleen als partnerrelatie bedoeld) komt elkaar tegemoet en weet wanneer met de persoon te communiceren en wanneer met het gedrag. verrijkende relaties maken het gevoel niet erger, maar verreiken elkaar dus 😍

omdat ik zelf vaak nog schrik van het egoisme en de macht die men probeert te onderhouden door gelijk op de eerste plek te zetten.

ooit sprak ik mijn eigen gevoelens eens uit aan iemand. maar in de plek dat er begrip kwam, werd het contact verbroken. het was mijn schuld 🤔🤣. een doordenker voor velen dus. 😄 en de oplossing ligt niet in labels. dat vertel ik in mijn nieuwste boek.

text: tensions are running high in india’s khasi community, one of the world’s few remaining matrilineal societies, as a new bill seeks to prevent women from marrying non-tribal members. based in the northeastern indian state of meghalaya, in the khasi tribe a family’s youngest daughter inherits her mother’s wealth and property.  children take their name and lineage from their mother’s side of the family. the new bill claims, that any khasi woman who marries a non-khasi, as well as her offspring born out of such marriages, shall be deemed as non-khasi. click the link in our bio to read why even groups fighting for more rights for men consider this bill hypocritical.

text:
"if you feel pain where the tendon (medial epicondyle) attaches to the inside of the elbow – that bumpy part that tingles when we knock it. chances are you are experiencing golfer elbow 🏌️‍♂️ .⠀
the main symptoms of golfers elbow are pain and tenderness around the bony bit on the inside of the elbow called the medial epicondyle, particularly when gripping hard with the hand. it is also not unusual to experience a general weakness in our wrists, with pain occurring when bending our wrist palm downwards against any resistance.⠀
.⠀
initially, the pain and inflammation can be relieved though the use of non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs based on you physician’s advice while applying the p.o.l.i.c.e principle;⠀
⠀
protection – protect the forearm / elbow / wrist from being aggravated further.⠀
.⠀
optimal loading – this means that rather than resting the elbow and waiting, recovery can be sped up by using the muscles affected at a restricted level to help stimulate the cells in the recovery process. this always prevents the muscles from weakening and shortening.⠀
.⠀
ice – use ice immediately after the injury occurs to prevent inflammation.⠀ .

compression – the use of a support or taping will help compress the affected area, immobilising and protecting it also.⠀
.⠀
elevation – elevate the hand /arm immediately to reduce pain and blood flow to the injured area.⠀ should your injury worsen over time or continue to cause you issues, physiotherapy is encouraged.⠀
.⠀
#golfelbow #golferelbow #elbowpain #elbow #medialepicondyle #metoo #value #sportsrehab #chiropractic #chiropractor #chirodoc”

text:
thank you to everyone who commented on my last post. thank you to everyone who dm’ed me. i have never felt so supported in my life, and i’m really grateful for all the amazing people in my life. 💗

i realized after this post that i’m not alone, and that there’s many people we see everyday who’ve been through similar things too, it’s horrible. i would never wish what happened to me to anyone else. 
this is to everyone who reached out to me and told me their stories, and to the people who are still alive with a lot of bad thoughts in their heads: you are strong. you are brave. and you don’t deserve what you’ve been through. never, not even for a second, think that what happened to you was your fault. i know how scary it can be to tell people what happened, i know how scary it can be thinking they won’t believe you. but you telling me was a really big step, and i’m proud of you. i’ll be here for anyone who wants to talk, it doesn’t matter if we don’t know each other, we’re stronger together. we can make the healing process easier for ourselves if we talk. 💜#neverstaysilent 
#metoo

text:
i read. i watch. internet. movies. news. and i think differently. each thing i learn alters my perception. #blacklivesmatter #blm changed me. #metoo changed me. did it change you? sure, you were aware of these things before. but i didn't really get it. i mean, really.

#trayvonmartin
#michaelbrown
#ferguson
#ericgarner

#blm founders; alicia garza, patrisse cullors, and opal tometi.

#metoo founder; tarana burke.

i watched it unfold. but i am still learning. in small things; like watching a movie and be like "this movie is about a woman who moves everytime a man leaves her and the fix to all this is... finding the perfect man?". i mean, really? it was hard ignoring things in the past, to enjoy a movie. today i'm like intelligently allergic. 
and bigger things; like watching white people call the police on black men and women who are just minding their own business. if it's a barbeque, a photo shoot in a park... it's unbelievable, yet i know better than to really say it's unbelievable. cause it happens all the time. all the time.

and the biggest things; black people being killed for no apparent reason. a black woman being pulled over by a traffic cop, only to die at the jail by hanging. #sandrabland #sandrastillspeaks #sayhername

or #samueldubose. i watched that video. the whole video. how the cop's statement of the events kept changing. as his own bodycam recorded everything.

google these hashtags. see for yourself. and just imagine; being the family of eg dubose. his death online for all eternity. sure, it's evidence. they don't have to guess. but still. his death is not just his; it's an injustice, another name on the list black people are fighting to keep from growing.

google #danielshaver. if you can stomach watching a man crawling down a hallway, begging for his life. then his body is riddled with bullets from a cop yelling orders at him.

then imagine being black and see this happen to people your color all the time. black bodies. white privilege. and then you hear people say "get over it", "slavery was a long time ago". you would get your game face on.

and metoo. was hijacked by white women. #intersectionaliy imhu; black women are black first.

text:
thrilled to welcome shelley bolton - the social entrepreneur behind the downtown-eastside's "east van roasters" to the panel for this year's women's awareness week for #iwd2019 in vancouver. .
.
n 2011, enticed by the challenge of bean-to-bar chocolate making and coffee roasting, shelley was recruited as director of social enterprise for the phs community services society to launch two employment programs for local women - the window community art shop and east van roasters. these programs are socially conscious businesses providing a compassionate work environment for women facing challenges in their lives. shelley is inspired every day by the dynamic and tenacious team of women she works alongside within the magical world of creating delicious and nourishing food.
.
. 
the well beings & weekend rituals (march 4, 9 & 10)
https://iwd2019vancouver.eventbrite.ca or the link in @minibarcanada's profile.

text:
did you know that i am an author?  at my former employment, we decided to write a question and answer book about self-injury.  when we had researched the books available, there were either textbooks reporting research or memoirs.  there was very little written for the individual, family, school, physician, therapist, or advocate.  so we wrote this book, “self-iniury: simple answers to complex questions”

this book is available on amazon in either paperback or kindle version.  just search the title or my name and you will find it. (please note i do not make any money off any purchases) 🧡

text: i know you’ve all probably seen this by now, as it’s been circling all over feminist pages. no matter how many times ive come across this the last day, my heart aches all over again. i was molested as a child. i don’t know what i would have done if it got to the point where i had to give birth to my abusers child. that young girl’s entire life was jeopardized for a baby that will spend its numbered days suffering. what if this was your daughter or little sister? please, for the love of god, stop subjecting children and women to such horrendous rape crimes, and please acknowledge the importance & necessity of our choice over our bodies. if you truly care about the number of abortions, donate towards organizations that offer free birth control, condoms, plan b, etc, and work as a society to improve the lives of lower income citizens. if unwanted pregnancies can be prevented or if raising children would be made easier for those who cannot afford to feed another mouth, the number of abortions will go down.

text:
you know those #proteinshakes that taste nasty and have a #chemicalaftertaste but are supposedely good for you, hmmmm? yea, #metoo the problem is i usually last about one try and then it sits there #foreverandalways never getting used again. then i try the chocolate one thinking that the chocolate taste will cover up the other stuff and i waste another pile of money. we've tried 4 or 5 different companies and i end up tossing it years later.
the reason why i share this is so you know that i'm not a big fan of these things. i even tried one that had the #coffee taste and i don't drink coffee. 
so here is my morning #breakfast or mid morning #hungercontrol snack, maybe even the mid afternoon snack. i mix it with tap water, drink it, and no gaging from the vanilla taste. i'm sure if i mixed it with milk or berries it would be even better, but #nobodygottimeforthat

text:
> nunca se me cruzó por la mente que mi madre tenía rasgos #feministas, porque -y para ser sincera- ni ella se identifica como tal, ni yo me había planteado. hasta que tuve una charla casual con una amiga. en dicha plática, me preguntó cómo y hace cuanto se habían conocido mis padres.

le conté que se conocieron a los quince, en una fiesta. pero comenzaron a salir a los dieciséis. y de ahí hasta los treinta y dos, 16 años… ¡que hasta parece obra del destino!... juntos, que no perfectos. eso sí, sin bebés o boda.

vaya, que todo esto salió porque en medio de la conversación, mi amiga dice: “¿cómo es posible?”, a lo que yo contesté, en modo broma: “mi mamá era una avanzada para su época”. pero a ella le hizo mucho sentido, y puede que sea cierto porque... joder… fueron 16 años antes de que llegaran niñxs o casamiento (que dicho sea de paso, fue únicamente por civil)... en inicios de los 80’s; toda una novedad considerando que de planificación familiar o anticonceptivos no se hablaba y que el quedarse embarazada para atar a un hombre a tu #vida es usado, bueno… hasta el día de hoy.

por otra parte…

que mi abuelo “peca” de machista, lo sabe cada individuo en mi casa. pero tal vez, las circunstancias, lo llevaron a incentivar el feminismo de mi madre. inconscientemente, claro está. ¿por qué? mi abuelo tenía una pequeña empresa de conducción de taxis, se separó de mi abuela cuando mi madre tenía diecisiete y mi madre era (y es) su única hija. eso trajo consigo que mi yeyo confiera mucho en ella, sobretodo en cuestiones administrativas; al mismo tiempo que le dió un oficio cuando le enseñó a manejar e hizo que sacara la licencia de conducir profesional.
.

tweet_full:
> nunca se me cruzó por la mente que mi madre tenía rasgos #feministas, porque -y para ser sincera- ni ella se identifica como tal, ni yo me había planteado. hasta que tuve una charla casual con una amiga. en dicha plática, me preguntó cómo y hace cuanto se habían conocido mis padres.

le conté que se conocieron a los quince, en una fiesta. pero comenzaron a salir a los dieciséis. y de ahí hasta los treinta y dos, 16 años… ¡que hasta parece obra del destino!... juntos, que no perfectos. eso sí, sin bebés o boda.

vaya, que todo esto salió porque en medio de la conversación, mi amiga dice: “¿cómo es posible?”, a lo que yo contesté, en modo broma: “mi mamá era una avanzada para su época”. pero a ella le hizo mucho sentido, y puede que sea cierto porque... joder… fueron 16 años antes de que llegaran niñxs o casamiento (que dicho sea de paso, fue únicamente por civil)... en inicios de los 80’s; toda una novedad considerando que de planificación familiar o anticonceptivos no se hablaba y que el quedarse embarazada para atar a un hombre a tu #vida es usado, bueno… hasta el día de hoy.

por otra parte…

que mi abuelo “peca” de machista, lo sabe cada individuo en mi casa. pero tal vez, las circunstancias, lo llevaron a incentivar el feminismo de mi madre. inconscientemente, claro está. ¿por qué? mi abuelo tenía una pequeña empresa de conducción de taxis, se separó de mi abuela cuando mi madre tenía diecisiete y mi madre era (y es) su única hija. eso trajo consigo que mi yeyo confiera mucho en ella, sobretodo en cuestiones administrativas; al mismo tiempo que le dió un oficio cuando le enseñó a manejar e hizo que sacara la licencia de conducir profesional.
.

text:
**the meat** (perhaps a poem?) can the meat feel?
its reality butchered
when it was a juicy calf 
naive with layers of fat 
it rang its bell and 
nudged its head,
feasting on grass all day and then
dreamt of grassy horizon at night.

i say the meat deserved the saw
ripe and ready for brine and broth

it thought of grass
when the butcher came
death was a shock,
it felt unreal.

the meat was preserved,
to be consumed by you.
that’s why it feels so cold.
every atom chilled to stillness,
perhaps time stands still as well.

the meat was butchered just yesterday,
the meat was butchered eons ago.
pain didn’t stop, there was no death
to save it from slaughter everyday.

you can dress the meat how you want,
just salt and pepper wouldn’t do though,
to hide its staleness you need the spice.

or maybe just grind it fine,
no one likes an empty krust.

a beast cannot give consent,
beastiality is rape for sure.
but consent is meaningless
for meat, it is just a thing

so, fuck the pie as you like
it’s not necrophilia,
just harmless banter.

did the meat give you a tummy ache?
poor baby, throw it in trash
it was rotting from inside
unsafe for consumption
down the chute it goes,
goodbye!

feeling a lump in your throat 
or perhaps a knot in the gut?

don’t be silly, bred for slaughter,
the meat deserves no empathy.

text:
tw sexual harassment, dysphoria 
the day was fine. really. a bit tiring maybe. i was waiting for my bus to the train station (we are going skiing ! yay !). there was this weird man at my stop but i tried to pay no mind. until that old man come to me and comments on my chest, ask me if i’m wearing a bra. and me, me who has been fighting for so many years the feminist fight, i lost all control : i screamed at him to get away, i threatened to call the police but for real, i was completely lost, suddenly i was as unprotected as when i was five, suddenly his cane was a weapon. never in my life did i feel dirty, ashamed, embarrassed and - fuck this is so twisted - responsible. i got into my bus. so did he. and when i got down, i cracked into tears and started drifting into dysphoria. this could be the end of the story, and i could still be crying. but i was pulled up by the nicest barista so now i remember : he is a jerk, an immonde man, he is the dirty one and i don’t have to feel embarrassed, ashamed and certainly not responsible. i know i’m supposed to know better. i just wish i knew how to react ... #sexualharrasment #dysphoria #tw #feminism #metoo

text:
so as i understand it, this brother had his entire life derailed, name dragged through the mud and never got his shot at the nfl because some woman lied and said he sexually assaulted her. and some of y’all are so trained by the media system that you run around saying when it comes to sexual abuse a woman wouldn’t lie smh. let’s be clear both men and women lie, because we’re flawed humans and there is sin that lives in all of our hearts. no i am not for supporting a system that forces women to suffer in silence while men abuse them for their own sick pleasures. i am also not for supporting a system that arms women with the power to destroy the livelihood and reputation of a man without a fair trial or without and repercussions if she is lying. in the last year we have seen tons of cases where a woman has falsely accused a man of some form of sexual assault. most of you like tag lines so much you don’t even stop to think about the ramifications of that tag line. people say “when a woman accuses a man of a crime you should believe her.” i say when a woman accuses a man you should believe her enough to demand a trial so that the facts can come out. when there is an accusation of a crime it is not our job to assume who the victim is but rather to tirelessly work towards truth and answers so that justice can be executed other wise we will once again build a system that rewards abusers and condemns victims... i know my opinion is not popular or being pushed by either of the idiot political parties so most will struggle to embrace it but let me remind you that you don’t have to embrace the options they give, there are other ways to think. i believe mine is a position of respect, love, truth and justice for both men and women which is what i stand for. 
#innocentuntilprovenguilty  #justiceforall #metoo 
#metoomovement #timesup #justiceformen #justiceforwomen #justiceforwomenandgirls

text:
•	should i still watch this show? pop culture in the #metoo era; tuesday, march 5, 12 p.m. - 1 p.m. in the student center conference room (stc 120)
in the wake of the #metoo movement, in which dozens of high-profile individuals in the entertainment industry have been accused of harassment or abuse, many of us are asking: “should i still be watching this?” explore the cultural and economic issues inherent in consuming entertainment made by people whose behaviors we find questionable, distasteful, or even criminal. media and feminism scholar amy peloff will ask important questions including: how do we weigh the cultural value of art against the behavior of the individual creating it? what do we think accountability in the #metoo movement should look like? do the decisions we make around our pop culture consumption even matter? join us for a conversation about the value of art and entertainment—and the value of being held to account.

text:
🅐🅢🅐🅟: 🅦🅞🅜🅔🅝 🅡🅘🅖🅗🅣🅢 ♀️😥
in 1948 un charter 🇺🇳 on human rights was signed and proclaimed equality,it promised same good existence for everyone. it is stated in article 1 of its charter is “тσ αcнιεvε ιηтεяηαтισηαℓ cσ-σρεяαтιση … ιη ρяσмσтιηg αη∂ εηcσυяαgιηg яεsρεcт ғσя нυмαη яιgнтs αη∂ ғσя ғυη∂αмεηтαℓ ғяεε∂σмs ғσя αℓℓ ωιтнσυт ∂ιsтιηcтιση αs тσ яαcε, sεx, ℓαηgυαgε, σя яεℓιgιση.” within the un’s first year, the economic and social council established its commission on the status of women, as the principal global policy-making body dedicated exclusively to gender equality and advancement of women. 
today there is also a lot of different ngos and international organisations which are  supposed to watch on women rights violation. it is important to admit, that however we usually associate feminism with western cultures, coming from “clubs for women in paris”, a big role in adding women’s right point into charter played women from all over the world. eleanor roosevelt is certainly the most famous of woman on the drafting committee, though also a big input is made thanks to minerva bernardino from the dominican republic, hansa mehta from india, and begum shaista ikramullah from pakistan. thanks to them we read it  in article 1 of the udhr, not the phrase “all men are born free and equal” but “all human beings are born free and equal.”
the charter was signed✔️ by 192 countries (2007), which is a significant change since 1948, when out of 58 members of un only 48❕ voted in favor of charter. 
today we might see the results, which have to make us think of feminism not as of an aggressive fight of “dissatisfied” women and “man-haters”, but of those who know, that the numbers are showing the basic human rights violation🤐😫😔:
countries with gender equality  112 😊
countries with no equality  77 😩
(gender inequality index 2017, undp / total 189 countries)
the 10 worst countries for gender equality🤯🤯🤯: yemen, pakistan, syria,  chad, iran , mali ,saudi arabia,lebanon, morocco, jordan
future is created today, future is already now.

text: former disney-pixar chief john lasseter, who has been accused of sexual misconduct, was, in a closely scrutinized move, put on leave from and then consulted for the company. he later took a head animation job at skydance media. on tuesday, actress emma thompson sharply criticized both lasseter and the company that hired him in a letter published in the @latimes. thompson dropped out of a film called “luck” shortly after the lasseter hiring, and the letter, to skydance chief executive and oracle scion david ellison, explains why she’s leaving the project. part of the letter reads: “if a man has been touching women inappropriately for decades, why would a woman want to work for him if the only reason he’s not touching them inappropriately now is that it says in his contract that he must behave ‘professionally’?” (photo by joel c ryan / invision / ap; illustration by @thelilynews)

text: i made a promise to myself that 2019 would be all about being uncomfortably vulnerable and perfectly-imperfectly human. i’ve been unlucky in love for most of my adult life because of either bad timing or mismatched compatibility, but mostly due to my own fears or dysfunction. this is what happens when you didn’t grow up with any healthy examples of lasting, loving relationships. but, to my credit, my intuition is also very strong, and ultimately, i’ve never betrayed it for very long. so, perhaps, god was simply preparing me for the rainbows after the storms- or simply allowing me the space to become a complete person without any crutches or safety nets. however, i’ve also been married to music and my artistic dreams ever since i can remember. so, in the form of lyric and melody of one of the purest songs that i’ve ever heard written about romantic love, here’s a piece of alexis strum’s “it could be you” on this most glorious day of our human existence. although, i’m fully committed to god, my spiritual journey, and being the best, most joyous and grateful for-all-that-i-have and not-what-i-don’t me possible, i’ll never stop having hope or believing in a romantic love with a soul mate that i can live out the rest of my days with and create (or re-create) my very own family. this circle completion would be greatly welcome and just as scarily daring as it is posting a video of me singing here without any production tricks, perfecting tools, or the usual smoke and mirror masks that we hide our insecurities behind. well, here i am: vulnerable, scared, and imperfect, but fully alive and ready for all that god has in store for me because that’s something that i’m also a true believer in based on a lifetime of miracles, healings, protection, new beginnings, and magical dream living. wishing the brightest hope, light and love-filled blessings for all of you resilient hearts out there today and always! #nevergiveup big hugs, cgun⚔️ #humanity #spiritualawakening #mystory #dreams #truth #light #love #music #art #artistsoninstagram #musiciansofinstagram #actorslife #writersofinstagram #metoo #timesup #blacklivesmatter #crisgunther #cgun #soberissexy @alexisstrum ✝️❤️

text:
i’m not saying it’s not possible to end up with another abusive, manipulative person, but that’s where self love/respect comes in. heal before you move on. set boundaries. getting into this marriage was a combination of being manipulated/played/tricked, but i was also naive, ignored red flags, let every boundary be pushed, didn’t listen to outside opinions of those closest to me, had an immense need to feel and be loved, hoped he’d revert back to who i met because that person was so awesome...and yeah. quite honestly, i don’t think anyone could be worse. and if i attracted someone similar, i learned how to run. you don’t need to be with someone, at least not so badly that you’d end up in another abusive relationship, but you also can’t be afraid to love again just bc the last douche was such a douche. .
.
.
.

text:
the hero:

the tendency to shut down was always there.
it was easier.
easier than facing the demons.
easier than coming to terms with all that had happened.
all of those things that couldn’t be controlled.
those things that harmed her so deeply...
creating fear, and distrust, and an anxious feeling that gnawed at her constantly, and made her want to run.
run...
run as far away as she could,
so she could be free of the pain.
so she never had to feel helpless again.
but what she didn’t realize is that she must face her darkness head on and look those demons straight in the eyes.
for this is how one heals.
this is how one makes peace with their past.
this is how one finally takes their power back and becomes the hero of their own life story.
#poetry #poetrycommunity #poet  #poetsofinstagram #poem #writerscommunity #writersofinstagram #writer #art #artistsoninstagram #artist #selflove #healing #recovery #depression #abusesurvivor #mentalhealthawareness #mentalhealth #thehero #saveyourself #metoo

tweet_full:
the hero:

the tendency to shut down was always there.
it was easier.
easier than facing the demons.
easier than coming to terms with all that had happened.
all of those things that couldn’t be controlled.
those things that harmed her so deeply...
creating fear, and distrust, and an anxious feeling that gnawed at her constantly, and made her want to run.
run...
run as far away as she could,
so she could be free of the pain.
so she never had to feel helpless again.
but what she didn’t realize is that she must face her darkness head on and look those demons straight in the eyes.
for this is how one heals.
this is how one makes peace with their past.
this is how one finally takes their power back and becomes the hero of their own life story.

text:
together we’ve made significant gains toward gender equality. we often get asked whether we still need #internationalwomensday... ...you know the answer. as events over the past year with #metoo and #timesup have reaffirmed, from the classroom to the boardroom, men’s sexuality continues to be prioritized over women’s and sexual violence remains a global epidemic.

we want a world where women are having sex in ways that they want to. not because they are being, coerced, forced or expected to. where the law respects and protects women and girls everywhere, from sexual violation and exploitation, from genital mutilation, from “child marriage”. where anyone who violates women and girls sexually is prosecuted. 
this coming week we’ll be sharing stories from our work to fight sexual violence and exploitation around the globe and the world we want for all women and girls—and how you can help us build it. 
#iwd2019 #endsexualviolence #thefutureisfemale

text:
“𝙸 𝚠𝚒𝚕𝚕 𝚗𝚘𝚝 𝚕𝚎𝚜𝚜𝚎𝚗 𝚖𝚢𝚜𝚎𝚕𝚏 𝚜𝚘 𝚝𝚑𝚊𝚝 𝚘𝚝𝚑𝚎𝚛𝚜 𝚌𝚊𝚗 𝚐𝚛𝚘𝚠.” 𝙸𝚜𝚜𝚞𝚎 𝚘𝚗𝚎: 𝙲𝚘𝚕𝚕𝚎𝚐𝚎, 𝚏𝚛𝚘𝚖 𝙳𝚞𝚜𝚔 𝚝𝚘 𝙳𝚊𝚠𝚗 @kokokourtney 🧡
.
.
i’ve had a “friend” in the past, and she was toxic. from the beginning when we met in fifth grade. it’s almost shocking that she’ll be the reason i’ll never be the way i once was. but aside from what she did that hurt the way i see myself, she was also a horrible friend. it’s about to get a bit sad, but that’s life. 🧡
.
.
it was always about her, and when i mention an accomplishment of mines to her, it was clear she didn’t want to hear it. i dim myself, and she, in her way, spark. i never had friends, and i felt i have to have her there with me. i wanted to look away from all the bad things she’s done to me and believe in a fucking lie. i have trust issues because of her. it took me a while before i finally realize, which prompted me to change myself, and my setting. it took time, and emotional outbursts and a fucking lake of tears, but i realized what i had to do. i couldn’t lessen myself, not for anyone. anyone who wants me to do that isn’t a friend. they’re foe. i don’t have many friends, and i’m happy with that. and i also know, i’m not going to be hesitant to cut people out if they think it’s all about them.🧡
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
it was such a pleasure chatting with becky, paul and shleigh, the creative force behind @showyourcourage_ , on #girlbonerradio.

inspired by dr. blasey ford's bravery, the trio created a rad symbol of support for sexual assault survivors. (see an image of the 😍 creation on my blog.) their messages of hope and advocacy are what so many of us need right now.

the episode also features thoughts from @dr.megan.fleming for a listener who wants to start dating again after healing work for trauma.

find highlights from our chat plus listening options at my profile link, or search for girl boner radio in your favorite podcast app!

#showyourcourage #girlboner #quotes #metoo #believewomen #healingfromabuse

text: “i assure you that no prophet is welcome in the prophet’s hometown. and i can assure you that there were many widows in israel during elijah’s time, when it didn’t rain for three and a half years and there was a great food shortage in the land. yet elijah was sent to none of them but only to a widow in the city of zarephath in the region of sidon. there were also many persons with skin diseases in israel during the time of the prophet elisha, but none of them were cleansed. instead, naaman the syrian was cleansed.” (luke 4:24-27) | a victim-survivor can breathe life into a church that is open to change, to developing safety against harm and understanding the tortures of nonphysical abuse. but a prophet in her hometown is not likely to perform such miracles. i am reminded of what jesus experienced for being outspoken and uncompromising on god's stance with the marginalized. his followers know to expect the same.

text:
#sisters are #strongertogether.⁣
i love all of my sisters. ⁣
⁣
i don't care about your race, ethnicity, religion, education, financial situation, birth place, sexual orientations or sexual adventures. ⁣
⁣
i love you all. ⁣
⁣
we all wake up every day and have a battle to fight in this world. ⁣
we are perceived as weaker, less intelligent, too emotional, and indecisive.⁣
⁣
if we wait to have sex we are stuck up. if we have sex "too soon" we are hoes.⁣
⁣
if we wear short skirts or nice underwear we have asked to be raped.⁣
⁣
if we come out against our rapist we want attention. if we wait too long to speak, it didn't happen. ⁣
⁣
if we cry, we're irrational. if we hold it together, we must be lying.⁣
⁣
our faces are never pretty enough, we are never the right body type and we never have the right size boobs or booty.⁣
⁣
but at the end up the day, we wake up, we rise up and we glow up. with our head, heels, standards and middle fingers held high. keep killing it ladies. i love y'all #wakeupriseupglowup .⁣
.⁣
.⁣
.⁣
.⁣

text:
the fight for equal wages and treatment in the workplace has been ongoing since the 1900s. unfortunately, women with disabilities have often been excluded from these conversations. women face 4% unemployment rate, while women with disabilities face 9.4%. according to the bureau of labor statistics, 68.6% of women without disabilities were hired in 2018, compared to 28% of women with disabilities. we must work to guarantee that these women’s voices are heard and they are not excluded. an inclusive society is one that is beneficial and considerate of all of its members, something we must continuously strive for. •
•

text:
meet nancy. she's awesome. and it's her birthday today. the three of us went on a tour around pai. it was a hoot

1. nikki wins the zolander prize and nancy enjoys her first trout pout
2. this is idea (bright boy) who drove us around, first in a songteauw bus but then in this honda dream machine which was a treat. no aircon, no seatbelts and the window winder handle (!) came off in my hand. we asked him to recommend somewhere with good wine and he got all flustered. it was only later when we realised that he thought we were propositioning him. poor lad, must have been terrified #metoo
3. next on the itinerary was visiting and swimming in a waterfall. however, it's been so dry up here that it has apparently disappeared so he took us to 'another one' which he promised was just over the bridge and down a bit. so we cross the ricketiest bamboo bridge, get down to our bathers and start wading. nope no waterfall, just fast moving river and lots of rocks. daft ferang women will never know the difference
4. big buddha with crazy snake like guardians
5. nikki and nancy doing eddie and patsy
6. buddha looks like a woman to me!
7. 196 steps up. and down! you can see our house from here
8. hot springs. bloody boiling springs more like. they got cooler as we moved down from pool to pool but the first one was uncomfortably hot. if it was a bath you'd give it half an hour before you got in
9. pai canyon. beautiful but really strange to see deciduous trees shedding their leaves in this heat
10. on our way back we saw this guy who'd been at the jazz club the night before. never seen the instrument before - like an electric double bass without it's body. you see all sorts on walking street

#ruthiesworldadventure #pai #bamboobridge #bigbuddhapai #paihotsprings #paicanyon #nancyrocks

text:
🌻 #thisisendometriosis @georgiewileman thank you for hosting this campaign to raise awareness for endometriosis and the length of time it takes to get diagnosed + all of the surgeries we must endure. ...
i personally have had 2 surgeries.  i would like to raise awareness for non-genetic forms of endometriosis.  my surgery in 2009 was an emergency surgery to repair a vaginal laceration from a sexual assault.  the physical trauma caused the tissue inside my body to grow abnormally and form endometrial lesions + adhere my organs. in 2016 i thought i was just having surgery to clean up the internal scar from the first surgery.  i had a laparoscopy, excision, and cystoscopy and was diagnosed with endometriosis by the amazing dr. nelson in colorado.  knowing that i will be in a lifetime of pain because of something someone else did to me is hard to deal with, especially on top of the pain.  but the silver lining is that my chronic pelvic pain caused me to start making cbd products that others now also use for their pelvic pain as alternatives to pharmaceuticals they try and force on us.  there are many barriers to access surgery and endometriosis experts, i hope in the future it’s easier to get diagnosed and that more natural options + excision are promoted more! & more accessible! xo alex 💛🌻🌻🌻
.
.
.

i personally have had 2 surgeries.  i would like to raise awareness for non-genetic forms of endometriosis.  my surgery in 2009 was an emergency surgery to repair a vaginal laceration from a sexual assault.  the physical trauma caused the tissue inside my body to grow abnormally and form endometrial lesions + adhere my organs. in 2016 i thought i was just having surgery to clean up the internal scar from the first surgery.  i had a laparoscopy, excision, and cystoscopy and was diagnosed with endometriosis by the amazing dr. nelson in colorado.  knowing that i will be in a lifetime of pain because of something someone else did to me is hard to deal with, especially on top of the pain.  but the silver lining is that my chronic pelvic pain caused me to sta making cbd products that others now also use for their pelvic pain as alternatives to pharmaceuticals they try and force on us.  there are many barriers to access surgery and endometriosis expes, i hope in the future it’s easier to get diagnosed and that more natural options + excision are promoted more! & more accessible! xo alex 💛🌻🌻🌻
.
.
.

text:
woohoo it's that time again y'all
it's plagiarize fridays!

cambridge says: it's to use another person's ideas or work and pretend that it is your own.
.
granted, creating content can be frustrating and increasing your visibility seems like more of the luck of the draw. but as a community of small business owners we have a moral responsibility towards each other which goes beyond money.
.
i recently had the privilege of listening to a business owner share her experience of how a customer came to their company with the competitors proposal for them to implement and how she not only turned him down but also told the competitor about it. naturally the client wasn't pleased but she felt like she didn't need to be an imposter to make money.
.
google says: an imposter is a person who pretends to be someone else in order to deceive others, especially for fraudulent gain.
.
***so here's some home work, think long and hard about plagiarism you might be unaware of. it can be as simple as a logo design or as big as someone's authentic point of view on a particular subject. i.e their brand voice.
.
the objective of this exercise is to get you as the client/ business owners to become alert to trends in trinidad you can avoid becoming a victim of (if you're not already)
.

text: i spent last night with a small and intimate group of gw students talking about how writing can be a tool in our healing from trauma. one of my favorite activities is having them walk around the room and answer these questions about what healing means to them and what about writing do they think could be healing for themselves. some of the responses to what healing means to them includes: “going to therapy”, “loving others and myself and the world”, “being around others laughing and smiling”, “refraining from judging myself for my emotional process”. this is a question that i learned to ask from @amitaswadhin and their mirror memoirs interviews and it’s always interesting to see that even for myself my answer changes so often throughout a single day.  thank you to gw for having me. if you know a group who would be interested in a writing and healing workshop, send me a message. ✨✨ #csa #ptsd #survivor #metoo

text:
- to a girl like you and me - 
to the girl who 
was too young 
too young to understand 
too young to know 
when he gave you a candy 
as his hands crept below 
to the girl who 
was too naïve 
had a glass too many “you’re safe with me,” he said 
as he poured another 
that rapist in disguise 
to the girl who 
couldn’t talk
he’d visit for a
week in a year “be nice to your uncle,” mom would say 
as he took her to the secluded park

to the girl who 
was too believing 
he said she got the job
invited her over for dinner
she was exhilarated 
until  she felt a hand on her bare thigh 
under the table 
what a bummer! 
to the girl who 
was afraid 
when he threatened 
to leak your videos 
so you held your wrist out 
used a blade 
to the girl 
whose story wasn’t told 
to the girl 
whose lips were sealed 
to the girl 
who couldn’t survive 
i’m sorry i cannot change history 
but i promise 
i promise in this better world 
in this brighter future 
stories will be told
lips won’t be sealed 
and girls like you 
will survive

text:
contest 4 of 2019.

contest alert for review of #metoobrutus by prana tharthiharan natarajan.

this wud be a month long contest .

the terms of the contest:

1. books are available as amazon purchase - the kindle edition of either of the two books – three halves and #metoo brutus. in the event that a participant reviews both books, each review will be treated as a separate entry.

2. the review must be posted on the amazon page with any star rating – starting from 1 star to 5 star. shud be honest reviews, not just 5-star ratings.

3. the contest must get at least 10 entries so that 1 grand prize is awarded – a month-long subscription of amazon kindle unlimited (or a gift voucher for that denomination)

4. the reviewers must post their review screenshot on the dyrt page on the comment section of this post with the relevant hashtags which will be communicated at the time of launching the contest.

5. the review should hopefully not give away spoilers, but should do justice to reviewing the whole content of the book, not just based on a glance of the first few chapters.

#didyoureadtoday #metoobrutus #contestalertindia #contestalertmumbai #contestalert #contest #bookreview

text:
-"i deserve better. i don't know where you get the idea that it's okay to treat me like how you are. further more, i don't understand how you even have the audacity to carry out that idea. you treat me like trash, tossing me whenever you find someone better. then, when you realize that person isn't the person who you thought they were, you bring me back in. you say sorry and do whatever you can to get me hooked again. no one deserves that, to be given false hope after disappointment over and over again. no one deserves to be lied to, to be placed as a sideline rebound, to be forgotten by someone who they genuinely thought cared." -just another woman
.

text:
stigma: a mark of disgrace associated with a particular circumstance, quality, or person
.
.
.
.
.
no matter how many figurative or literal miles one can travel, there is always a stigma of living with scars people cannot see, and constantly have to explain. i am reminded every day that i am not whole, whether it be the companion of constant ringing in my ears, emotional scars or the ones we wear from our own expectations and failures. stigmas weigh on your heart, and your mind. a cross you unintentionally are forced to bare. but i hope if you’ve survived something, live with something, are going through something, that you find those moments that remind you that you are not your experiences. you’re never defined by your scars. you are the only one who can give validation to your life. and i hope you know, you’re not alone. .
.
.
.
.

text:
freedom is waking up every day to a new possibility. each moment there is a new reality to be created. freedom is not being tied to any old ideas or situations. it is complete self-determination. with this freedom is great responsibility. it means that only you are accountable for the occurrences in your life. you cannot blame anyone else; that is giving away your freedom, saying that someone or something else has the power of determination over you. it takes enormous courage to shoulder this responsibility every moment of every day. there are bound to be moments of self-doubt, of fear even. you must either carry the immense weight of constant choice that total freedom confers or abdicate to live in a cage of your own making. this path is frightening, exhilarating, liberating. it is not for the feint of heart or the weak willed. when you pass a fellow traveler, embrace them and rejoice. help make the journey a little easier and more loving.
*photographer: @lexonart
*model: @itsirisa
*

text:
ladies- the news, tv, ads... all propogate to women from an early age that we will never be loved or validated w/o physical (sexual) approval. once we realize it's bullsh*t & begin to raise each other up, we take our power back. ...that photo is me at about 14. that's my artwork flanking me. youngest of 3 girls, i had already owned the dialogue society was brainwashing me with: that i wasn't enough, that women were less. took a long while to wake up from that fog. some never do. we need eachother ladies... i'd be lying if i didn't recognize that the quality of my life, my career and my relationships would be better had i learned this lesson earlier in life. i needed good role models! let's be those role models for the generations to follow us. let's help & support one another.
(#flashback)
🧡
#timesup #metoo #strongwomen #women #womenempowerment #wisdom #girls #empowerment #success #womeninfilm #rolemodel #werise

text:
it's madeleine @m_p_corcoran here, continuing this #ffconversation between myself, pia johnson @piajohnsonphotography  and ingrid levya @ingridlv. we'll be creating this dialogue until the end of tomorrow (saturday). in response to your images, i'd like to share this one from my photo-poem, 'you did this to yourself' which explores and exposes the myths surrounding sexual violence. a change in tone but there's a connection here pia with your image - your idea of performing the myth of an identity and trying to find a more nuanced definition.

this piece is a response to some documents of sexual violence (court transcripts, news reports, interviews with victims). it is a critique of the myths that surround our understanding of sexual violence. each image tries to explore the latent emotions and meanings of the verbatim text. i wanted to find a way to expose the human crisis of sexual violence without making it about exposing victims as 'symbols' of rape. i feel like a lot of discussion around sexual violence centres on revealing victims, even if sympathetically - and my concern is to move beyond this potentially voyeuristic focus on the victim. sexual violence is recognised as a human rights issue when we all care about it, not when we believe that only victims should care. 
this is one image from the film sequence. i also made a book. you can see more of the piece on my instagram profile in my highlights and posts. also, it was recently a part of 'let's talk about sexual violence' http://www.talksv.uk/ - a great project and exhibition about sexual violence created by @kajalnp that brings together art, education, and advocacy.

#metoo #sexualviolence #survivor #myth #humanrights #thisisnotconsent #metoomovement #ffconversation #womeninphoto #piajohnson #madeleinecorcoran #ingridleyva

text:
here, cylindrical netherworlds elevate themselves and alleviate their restraints to a place where begotten 
factions of forever cannot be understated; in this place sits a girl with a forgotten face and an eye for hell. 
the product of everything that has gone before and is to come, she is but the sum of herself and the equation of many

men who came before.

text:
jak człowiek chce sobie życie ułatwić to wczorajszą zupę poda w zupełnie innej formie tak żeby potomstwo się nie pokapowało i zjadło ze smakiem 😂. wystarczyło krupnik zmiksować, wrzucić groszek ptysiowy i voila. na pietruszkę już zgody nie było, ale sobie nie żałowałam, zielone to bym mogła jeść bez umiaru 😉😁🌱. zaczęłam właśnie czytać książkę od @wydawnictwomuza i powiem wam, że dobra rzecz. pomyśl, że wolno ci wypowiedzieć tylko 100 słów dziennie 😱. dlaczego? bo jesteście kobietą, a rząd skazuje połowę społeczeństwa na milczenie. na ręku metalowa bransoletka liczy twoje słowa, gdy przekroczysz limit silny ładunek elektryczny paraliżuje twoją dłoń. nie mówisz i nie możesz pisać. wyobrażacie sobie taką rzeczywistość❌? człowiek średnio używa 16 tysięcy słów dziennie. jak zatem zmieścić się w 100 ? jestem mega ciekawa tej powieści. jem, czytam i robię koc na zmianę 🤣, taki piątek. zatem miłego popołudnia 😘, weekend tuż tuż 😁.
.
.

text:
hiiiiii.....⠀
⠀
what have you been up to? i have been scheduling in some writing as part of my daily routine. it is the month of march so my reflection has been on business, since i started sharisse hosein ltd in 2013, end of march. i am also celebrating being a migrant woman in business for 2 years in the u.k. ⠀
⠀
.⠀
.⠀
.⠀
i also want you to know that using social media for me has been liberating over the last couple years. i literally went from camera shy, to "camera shine." i just felt so comfortable talking to my inner circle - my facebook group that i just posted random things all the time. i really really loved sharing my insights, my experiences but here's what, i shared very little emotion with you. this is something i want to change this year and i am working on it. ⠀
⠀
.⠀
.⠀
.⠀
another very very important aspect in my life that i have been reflecting on is the type of woman i am, the role i play in my community and well, the online community especially. this leads me to focus on the relationships i have built. the thing is some of those relationships i once left behind in trinidad were toxic, and my return challenged me with memories of these experiences. some people can be so unkind and unloving, though at times they were right about my personality, i often felt isolated. when i think about the struggles i faced in my career, growing up in a very aggressive and violent society, it is overwhelming. my sensitivity may have left me alone at times processing all these emotions. that's why i always felt i was more introverted, but the truth is i am expressive too. ⠀
⠀
over the years, i was able to process my emotions and challenges with relationships with a professional. i developed an appreciation for my clinical practice, but moreso, for the freedom to have my own business. when i pursued my mba, of course, i could not leave my passion for people behind. i embraced my understanding of  the power behind emotional recognition. ⠀
.⠀
.⠀
. ⠀
⠀
my friend gave me this brilliant idea of starting a movement or building a concept. 
to join the inner circle on facebook check the link above. 
happy reflecting in march. ⠀
#reflection #balanceforbetter ⠀

text:
friendship is not what we see these days. a few people hanging out together or partying all day. friendship is when you can blindly trust someone.. when you know no matter what you have someone always by your side.. when you know you are loved, cared for and you matter to a soul... when you know there is someone who can't afford to loose you... when you can bet on them just as you can bet on your ownself... friendship is much more than giving treats and posting images together ... it is built on pillars of love, respect, trust, happiness and care. .
.
.
.
.
.
.

i love you friend @palakg_1111  and i can't afford to loose you ever ❤️. .
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
. .

text: i remember the first time “it happened”..... correction the darkness of the sexual abuse that was done to me as a child.  the world was shut off from the darkness of what was going to happen to me..... another persons  choice to put there darkness on me happened.  in that moment i started to allow my light of innocence get held within me from the darkness of shame.  i hid the light covering it with food, codependency and porn.  yes porn one of the most consumed forms of media today and if you never looked at it 🤔 congratulations on that. i wanted to stop using these substances as my light.  i allowed that to be my reality for years and years of my life.  on the outside i seemed just fine but in reality i was in utter pain.  one day i had enough of where i was at i left a religion that i allowed to cast darkness on my life.  i wanted the true light that was in me not masked with the substances of this world.  when i was finally done being fake and wanted to be truly me i began my journey to unlock me.  there had been many tears to rid this darkness and family members lost who have shunned me for this action.  today in this moment i am genuinely ok with it and there decisions.  why?  i have the self worth to be myself and whatever cost it might cost me.  i know what it cost not being me and i will never go back to that darkness.  #ubu #metoo #metoomovement #bully #abuse #emotionalabuse #raiseyourvibe #god #religion #now #change #anxietyrelief #depression #me #motivation #soberlife #overeatersanonymous #recoverylife #codependency #codependentnomore #parenting #parenthood #mentalhealthawareness #discoverlloydminster #lsas

text:
#metoo është një lëvizje globale e cila solli bashkë qindra e mijëra gra, të ndanin publikisht përvojat e tyre rreth ngacmimeve dhe sulmeve seksuale apo të mbështetnin këtë kauzë nëpërmjet përfshirjes në fushatë. 
ymca në shqipëri i bashkohet kësaj nisme, duke ftuar meshkujt të sensibilizohen dhe bëhen pjesë e fushatës për të treguar që të gjithë jemi kundër dhunës me bazë gjinore. me moton “meshkujt kundër dhunës me bazë gjinore” ne ftojmë të gjithë meshkujt, djemtë dhe burrat të kontribuojnë duke bërë një foto me hashtag #metoo dhe duke nominuar 3 meshkuj të tjerë të bëjnë të njëjtën gjë. hashtag-et që do të përdoren janë: #metoo #y_men_against_gender_based_violence #ymcatirana_albania
fushata do të zgjasë deri në datën 7 mars dhe në datë 8 mars ju ftojmë të na bashkoheni në marshimet që do të organizohen në tiranë dhe qytete të tjera.

#metoo is a global movement against sexual harassment and sexual assault initiated by women. ymca joins this campaign with the motto "men against gender based violence" and invites all men to get engaged and to contribute by taking a photo using the hashtag #metoo and nominating 3 other men to do the same. other hashtags are: #metoo #y_men_against_gender_based_violence #ymcatirana_albania

text: in this article, we see 2 separate instances of children being abused by their parent's or guardian's lovers. and, while we aren't shaming the mom or grandmother, we have to have the conversation about who you're allowing around your kids and just how much unsupervised access do they have. how well do you really know your boyfriend or girlfriend? do you really know if they are capable of sexually abusing your child? is it really safe for them to be around your children unsupervised? is it really safe for them to move in with you and your children? too many children are sexually abused by their parent's boyfriend/girlfriend or live-in lover. therefore, there is no such thing as being too careful when it comes to the safety of your kids! no matter how well you think you know someone; how "nice" they are, or how well they seem to act around your kids, you really can't be sure they are safe until you've had ample time to vet them. and even then, you should still be careful because predators are extremely patient and masters of manipulation and deception. even a person who considers themselves to be a pretty good judge of character will find themselves duped by these chameleons. and, because love, lust, and even like can cloud judgement and dull intuitions, we beg you to err on the side of caution for your child's sake. so much of this abuse can be prevented by limiting access to your child to others. these predacious monsters prey on those whom appear vulnerable and they appear as knights in shining armor, but under the surface, their intentions are vile. please take heed....they all seem safe until they aren't. #childsexabuseawareness #stopchildsexabuse #childsexabusesurvivor #parentsofchilldsexabusesurvivor #sexualassault #endchildsexabuse #endrapeculture #childabuse #sextrafficking #atlanta #atl #georgia #church #girls #teens #awareness #rapevictim #victim #children #prevention #trafficking  #survivor #tips #blogger #speaker #metoo #advocate #volunteer #activist #socialmedia

text:
“the more the #metoo movement was happening, the more i saw men in my life retract. i have two brothers, the majority of my cousins are boys. it’s normal for me to be in a space with men, but for a lot of women it’s triggering. [for this workshop, i thought] what would it be like to lead a group of men — as a woman of color in maine — and just say you guys can come as you are? to be willing to look at who you are right now? 
we’re all in this transition, how can we be okay with not really knowing what to do?” pearls of portland 016 is anne esguerra, certified yoga therapist with integrative life therapy (@horizonlinexploretheconnection)

supporting in conjuction with @comicrelief #comicrelief • • • • • do not  give ne money to these #fakecharities . we have seen what they did in #haiti n continue to do all over #africa ➕who has seen any difference they have made? have been on #tv since i was growing up ➕the only difference we see is what @akon has done. well done @david_lammy
for having the courage to stand up to such. 🗽 we want more ppl #like you... ☵ need to ask, once you hear this story, where do ugandan girls fit into your #metoo and #timesup movements? it seems that much of the time, the only stories you care about spreading are those with fame, power or influence... and we know, most especially, wyt women.
•2day we are asking you to listen to the stories of countless #ugandan women and girls who have endured hell at the hands of a white, #belgian citizen by the name of bery glaser.
•in 2013, mr. glaser was arrested for these same allegations, however, the girls who were living at his home “bery’s place” in kalangala - they had nowhere else to go, no way to continue paying for school fees, and so when it came time for court, they did not feel safe enough to testify.
•
this time must be different. after being arrested in 2013, mr. glaser was able to return to the home in kalangala and allegedly has continued to exploit and abuse many of the underage girls in his “care”.
•
yesterday, 24th february 2019, uganda police went to kalangala to arrest mr. glaser — he escaped, his whereabouts currently unknown, however they were able to arrest his wife.
•
we need you to share this story with the hashtag #kalangalatoo — we need to stand together to bring this man to justice.
•
we are also collecting donations to meet the immediate needs of the girls — there “support” has been taken away as of yesterday and we are asking for all to pitch in where they can to meet their immediate needs.
•

text:
so it’s #fearlessfriday already and there’s something i’ve felt necessary to share with y’all for a while, but haven’t had the courage. it’s scary how people will react to personal trauma, but that’s what i’m trying to fight with only yes means yes. so here goes nothing. my first #metoo moment. 
my sophomore year of college i went out to watch some ufc fight (not that i care about it at all lol). a friend of mine and i went to a house with a guy i knew. there were lots and lots of people there. after the fight we walked downtown and danced for a bit and then headed back to her dorm. 
he had been drinking so he was just going to stay with us. she headed up to her bed as i cozied up on some beanbags on the floor. he was further away but kept inching closer to me. he started touching me and trying to kiss me and i kept saying “stop, i have a boyfriend. i don’t want to do this.” but he pinned me down, and did things that i clearly did not want to do. i cried and pleaded for him to stop, but he wouldn’t. 
i then tried to crawl up into my friend’s bed, but she told me “no, you’re such a slut. how could you do that when you’re in a relationship?” i searched for my keys, but they grabbed them and hid them from me so i couldn’t even get out. i eventually found them and ran out of the dorms. he followed. saying he needed a ride. he sat in my car and told me we had this undeniable connection. “you raped me.” i said.
“what? what do you mean? are you accusing me of something? i did you a favor. we just have this connection, hayley.” he said.
he sat there for at least an hour not listening to a word i said about him getting out of my car and completely ignoring the fact that i was traumatized. at this point it was four in the morning and i was exhausted. i couldn’t even go back to my apartment. i drove all the way home to my mom’s house an hour away. i told her everything. finally, someone believed me. 
the trauma from this event haunts me every day. sometimes a little touch or a phrase can trigger me. it’s never going to be easy. it’s so hard to share. this was just the first time. the second is much harder for me to talk about. i just felt it necessary that other

text: march 1st is self-injury awareness day.  self-injury, also known as nonsuicidal self-injury (nssi) is when one purposely harms themselves as a way to cope with their feelings or thoughts.  a common form of self-injury is cutting although there are many other ways to injure.  the idea of purposely hurting oneself to feel better does not make logical sense.  however, for someone who may feel numb, disconnected from their emotions, or dealing with something beyond what they have skills to do so, self-harm can seem to work in the moment.  self-injury is an in-the-moment short-term solution that has more negative consequences in the long-term than it has positive.  it can be difficult to stop injuring - especially since the healthy ways to cope do not bring immediate relief.  there is help for those who self-injure and there is life after self-injury 🧡

hi ghana education service, it’s come to our attention that one of your teachers posted this in a facebook group. these kinds of “jokes” not only promote rape culture, but are very telling of the pervasiveness of pedophilia, and sexual violence in the teaching and education community. as the body in charge of the safety of our children against predators, and abuse, we expect you to do better. these are criminal cases, and should be treated as such. in any other conscious and child friendly society, ghana police service ghana police would follow up on such utterances. 
to the admins of large groups, do some really good introspection about why you think it’s good to allow your platforms to be used in the propagation of rape culture and pedophilia. there are thousands of adults (former children) on your platforms of whom many have been abused, assaulted, raped, etc. allowing such jokes on your platforms whether you like it or not, triggers many. be sensitive to those on these platforms. 
and to anyone who thinks these issues are not serious enough to be fealty with by regulatory and security bodies, you are the problem. 
#ocvteam

前回の休職時、本当に家の中でお風呂のお湯がドロドロに濁っていたり、不眠になり病院に行こうとしたら保険証がなくなってて行けなかった。すぐに見つかったが、会社の名札も同時に無くなった。
これは未だに見つかっていない。
多加子にももちろん話した結果警察には言わず
病院に強制的に連れていかれた。
もちろん病院に行かないといけない精神状態だったが、家の件は何もしていないはず。
なぜ警察に行かなかった？
1番疑ってるのは家の中の不審な事が今回と同じという事。
ヤンマーが仕掛けているのはほぼ確実。
多加子は会社と私が精神的におかしいのが原因と勝手に話をつけたのではないかと思っている。
いつも多加子が私の人生の岐路で間違った選択をさせる。今回も。
そして挙げ句の果てに全部妄想という回答をしてきた。
妄想ではありません。これが現実。
あなたが私の家計状況を拡散させたのも現実です。
病院に行くのも必要だけど、なぜそうなったかを考えたか？
解決しようとしたか？
今更私や娘の家族で何でも知ってる感出して名乗り出てくる。
何も知らないふりして犯人と話しをする
お前は私たち家族の関係よりも自分の体裁を選んだ。
母には言ったが、家族でもない、人間でもないと言う言葉は今後どれだけ罪を償ったとしても二度と撤回しない。

text: i’m accountable || i have been on both sides of domineering masculinity, and both have made me feel like filth. i am not going to say “me too” because as a heterosexual man i have not experienced the daily abuse that any female human undoubtedly has. but i have had my dignity stripped away by other men, who saw my anima and my body as something that was theirs for the taking. at times it was so bad that i have felt less than a cockroach. however, i have been on the other side of the equation, and i deserve to feel like a cockroach. i am responsible and accountable for the ways i have abused women - for inflicting the same abuse i have received. whether it was direct abuse, or ignorance, i am aware that i am fully to blame. for a time now i have tried my absolute best to actively right these wrongs i have committed. and over time one thing has become painfully clear - that an entire lifetime of actively standing against misogyny will not right my wrongdoings. but a lifetime is all i have - and i can, will, and am doing what is within my power to make this world i love a better place for every human. i will not live to see the day when every person is just a person, without label or judgment, but i can stand united with what is just and use my voice, my art, and my soul to set the wheel in motion. whoever you are, wherever you are, if you stand for something, stand for humanity. remember, we are all in this together, and love is the only answer. #metoo #accountability #loveistheanswer

text:
i recently got diagnosed with endometriosis; a condition where the tissue from the uterus doesn't flush during menstruation but manifests around the reproductive organs and develops scar tissue. it hurts like a muddafukka and is a chronic condition. do you experience extreme abdominal pain the days before and during menstruation? do you feel a kind of stinging pain around your bladder/ rectum during menstruation, or pain around your ovaries during ovulation? up to 30% of people with uteruses have endometriosis, but only 10% experience symptoms and only 6% are treated (in dk). if you suffer from severe menstruation cramps, maybe you have endometriosis too: don't feel weak, embarrassed or hysterical if the pain is sometimes too crazy to handle. i feel it too fam. endometriosis can effect your fertility, and in extreme cases, the tissue travels to heart and lungs and can therefore be life threatening. unfortunately as with all womxn's health issues, there has been done little research on the field, and is there for only treated with hormones (in form of p pills and hormone ui, which  often causes depression and other mental health issues). take care of yourselves 💉❣️ .🍍
.🍍
.🍍

text: brave shared her story with us but requested to be anonymous , this is #herstory .  iʼm a s.u.r.v.i.v.o.r !!!!!! no i didnʼt survive some awful disease or condition. i survived being raped as a teenager by some dirty man in a dirty garage. i was a foolish teenager who thought that my no meant no. i only told a few friends at school what happened to me and i kept it hidden and buried until now . as a result of the rape i became promiscuous because i made up in my mind that no one would be able to take anything from me ever again without my permission. i hadnʼt let jesus in my heart yet and now i know that it was him that protected me during that horrible time . he thought of me even though i wasn’t thinking of him . it took many years to open my heart to jesus but i’m glad i did . it took some years of living on the edge to finally be surrendered to jesus. the #metoo movement means so much to me because it happened to me too ! me telling my story doesn’t erase what happened but me sharing it releases the hold it has on me and with the help of jesus i can finally move forward. this is #herstory so what’s yours ?#hsm#herstory #herstorymovement #women4christ
